<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimine ja p&auml;randaja </eesti>
<inglise>Succession and bequeather </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;rimine on isiku surma korral tema vara &uuml;leminek teisele isikule. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Succession is the transfer of the property of a person upon his or her death to another person. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&auml;randaja on isik, kelle vara tema surma korral teisele isikule &uuml;le l&auml;heb. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A bequeather is a person whose property transfers upon his or her death to another person. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rand </eesti>
<inglise>Estate </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rand on p&auml;randaja vara. </eesti>
<inglise>An estate is the property of a bequeather. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randiks ei ole p&auml;randaja &otilde;igused ja kohustused, mis seadusest tulenevalt v&otilde;i oma olemuselt on lahutamatult seotud p&auml;randaja isikuga. </eesti>
<inglise>An estate does not include the rights and obligations of the bequeather which pursuant to law or by their nature are inseparably bound to the person of the bequeather. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randi avanemine </eesti>
<inglise>Opening of succession </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;rand avaneb p&auml;randaja surma v&otilde;i surnuks tunnistamise korral. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A succession opens upon the death or declaration of death of the bequeather. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&auml;randi avanemise aeg on p&auml;randaja surmap&auml;ev. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The time of opening of a succession is the date of death of the bequeather. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) P&auml;randi avanemise koht on p&auml;randaja viimane elukoht. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The place of opening of a succession is the last residence of the bequeather. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) P&auml;randi avanemisel tekib p&auml;rijal &otilde;igus p&auml;rida. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Upon the opening of a succession, a successor has the right to succeed. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tmine </eesti>
<inglise>Acceptance of succession </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimiseks peab p&auml;rija p&auml;randi vastu v&otilde;tma. </eesti>
<inglise>In order to succeed, a successor must accept the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimisv&otilde;ime </eesti>
<inglise>Succession capacity </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;rimisv&otilde;ime on isiku v&otilde;ime p&auml;rida. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Succession capacity is the capacity of a person to succeed. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&auml;rimisv&otilde;imeline on iga &otilde;igusv&otilde;imeline isik. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Any person with passive legal capacity has succession capacity. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) P&auml;rija v&otilde;ib olla f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik, kes p&auml;randaja surma ajal on elus, v&otilde;i juriidiline isik, kes sel ajal on olemas. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A natural person who is alive at the time of death of the bequeather or a legal person who exists at that time may be a successor. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) P&auml;rast p&auml;randi avanemist elusalt s&uuml;ndinud laps loetakse p&auml;randi avanemise ajal p&auml;rimisv&otilde;imeliseks, kui ta oli eostatud enne p&auml;randi avanemist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A child born alive after the opening of a succession shall be deemed to have succession capacity at the time of opening of the succession if the child was conceived before the opening of the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Sihtasutus, mis luuakse testamendi v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepingu alusel, loetakse p&auml;randi avanemise ajal olemas olevaks, kui ta hiljem omandab juriidilise isiku &otilde;igused. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A foundation established by a will or testamentary contract shall be deemed to exist at the time of opening of the succession if it acquires the rights of a legal person later. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimisk&otilde;lbmatus </eesti>
<inglise>Unworthiness to succeed </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;rimisk&otilde;lbmatu on isik, kes: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person is unworthy to succeed if the person: </inglise>
<eesti>1) on toime pannud p&auml;randaja v&otilde;i eelp&auml;rija vastu suunatud nende surmaga l&otilde;ppenud isikuvastase kuriteo, v&auml;lja arvatud h&auml;dakaitses v&otilde;i h&auml;dakaitsepiire &uuml;letades toimepandu; </eesti>
<inglise>1) commits a criminal offence against the person of the bequeather or provisional successor resulting in their death except if committed in self-defence or in excess of the limits of self-defence; </inglise>
<eesti>2) teadvalt ja seadusevastaselt asetas p&auml;randaja olukorda, milles ta kuni oma surmani oli v&otilde;imetu tegema v&otilde;i muutma viimse tahte avaldust; </eesti>
<inglise>2) knowingly and unlawfully places the bequeather in a situation where he or she is incapable of making or altering a testamentary disposition until his or her death; </inglise>
<eesti>3) sunni v&otilde;i pettusega takistas p&auml;randajat tegemast v&otilde;i muutmast viimse tahte avaldust v&otilde;i samal viisil sundis teda viimse tahte avaldust tegema v&otilde;i muutma, kui p&auml;randajal ei olnud v&otilde;imalik oma tegelikku viimset tahet v&auml;ljendada; </eesti>
<inglise>3) by duress or deceit hinders the bequeather from making or altering a testamentary disposition or in the same manner induces the bequeather to make or alter a testamentary disposition if it is no longer possible for the bequeather to express his or her actual testamentary intention; </inglise>
<eesti>4) teadvalt ja seadusevastaselt k&otilde;rvaldas v&otilde;i h&auml;vitas testamendi v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepingu, kui p&auml;randajal ei olnud enam v&otilde;imalik seda uuendada. </eesti>
<inglise>4) knowingly and unlawfully removes or destroys a will or testamentary contract if it is no longer possible for the bequeather to renew it. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Isikul ei ole &otilde;igust p&auml;rida selle isiku vara, kelle vastu ta on toime pannud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud teo. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person does not have the right to succeed to property of a person against whom the person has committed an act specified in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Lapse seadusj&auml;rgseks p&auml;rijaks ei saa olla tema vanem, kellelt kohus on vanema &otilde;igused &auml;ra v&otilde;tnud. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The parent of a child whom a court has deprived of parental rights cannot be an intestate successor of the child. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi s&auml;tteid kohaldatakse ka annakusaajate ja teiste isikute suhtes, kellel on &otilde;igus saada p&auml;randist mingit kasu. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The provisions of this section also apply to legatees and other persons who have the right to receive benefit from the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimisk&otilde;lbmatuse tagaj&auml;rjed </eesti>
<inglise>Consequences of unworthiness to succeed </inglise>
<eesti>Kui p&auml;rija on p&auml;rimisk&otilde;lbmatu, on p&auml;rima &otilde;igustatud see isik, kes oleks p&auml;rinud siis, kui p&auml;rimisk&otilde;lbmatu isik oleks surnud enne p&auml;randi avanemist. </eesti>
<inglise>If a successor is unworthy to succeed, the person who would have succeeded if the unworthy person had died before the opening of the succession is entitled to succeed. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimisk&otilde;lbmatuks tunnistamise hagemine </eesti>
<inglise>Action for declaration of unworthiness to succeed </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vaidluse korral v&otilde;ib kohus tunnistada isiku p&auml;rimisk&otilde;lbmatuks huvitatud isiku n&otilde;udel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In the case of a dispute, a court may declare a person unworthy to succeed at the request of an interested person. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud n&otilde;ude aegumist&auml;htaeg on kuus kuud p&auml;rimisk&otilde;lbmatuse p&otilde;hjustest teada saamisest, kuid mitte pikem kui 10 aastat p&auml;randi avanemise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The limitation period of a claim specified in subsection (1) of this section is six months after becoming aware of the reasons for unworthiness to succeed, but not longer than ten years from the date of opening of the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimise alused </eesti>
<inglise>Bases for succession </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;rimise aluseks on seadus (seadusj&auml;rgne p&auml;rimine) v&otilde;i p&auml;randaja viimne tahe, mis on avaldatud testamendis (p&auml;rimine testamendi j&auml;rgi) v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepingus (p&auml;rimine p&auml;rimislepingu j&auml;rgi). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The basis for succession is law (intestate succession), the testamentary intention of the bequeather expressed in a will (testate succession) or a testamentary contract (succession by testamentary contract). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&auml;rimis&otilde;igust p&auml;rimislepingu j&auml;rgi eelistatakse p&auml;rimis&otilde;igusele testamendi j&auml;rgi, neid m&otilde;lemaid aga p&auml;rimis&otilde;igusele seaduse j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The right of succession by testamentary contract is preferred to the right of succession by will, but both of these are preferred to the right of succession by law. </inglise>
<eesti>2. osa </eesti>
<inglise>Part 2 </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimine seaduse j&auml;rgi </eesti>
<inglise>Intestate Succession </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Seadusj&auml;rgse p&auml;rimise kohaldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Application of intestate succession </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;ritakse seaduse j&auml;rgi, kui p&auml;randaja ei ole j&auml;rele j&auml;tnud kehtivat testamenti v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepingut. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Succession is intestate if the bequeather has not left a valid will or testamentary contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui p&auml;randaja testament v&otilde;i p&auml;rimisleping k&auml;ib ainult p&auml;randi osa kohta, p&auml;ritakse &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;nud osa seaduse j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the will or testamentary contract of a bequeather only concerns a share of the estate, the remaining share is succeeded to in intestacy. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Seadusj&auml;rgsed p&auml;rijad </eesti>
<inglise>Intestate successors </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Seadusj&auml;rgsed p&auml;rijad on p&auml;randaja abikaasa ja k&auml;esolevas seaduses nimetatud sugulased. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Intestate successors are the bequeather's spouse and the relatives specified in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 18 s&auml;testatud alusel on seadusj&auml;rgne p&auml;rija kohalik omavalitsus&uuml;ksus v&otilde;i riik. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The intestate successor is a local government or the state on the basis provided for in &sect; 18 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>Sugulased seadusj&auml;rgsete p&auml;rijatena </eesti>
<inglise>Relatives as intestate successors </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Sugulased p&auml;rivad kolmes j&auml;rjekorras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Relatives succeed in three orders. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teise j&auml;rjekorra p&auml;rijad p&auml;rivad, kui esimese j&auml;rjekorra p&auml;rijaid ei ole. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Second order successors succeed if there are no first order successors. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kolmanda j&auml;rjekorra p&auml;rijad p&auml;rivad, kui esimese ja teise j&auml;rjekorra p&auml;rijaid ei ole. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Third order successors succeed if there are no first or second order successors. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Sugulaste seadusj&auml;rgse p&auml;rimise kohta k&auml;ivaid s&auml;tteid kohaldatakse, arvestades k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 16 s&auml;testatud p&auml;randaja &uuml;leelanud abikaasa &otilde;igust p&auml;randile. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The provisions concerning intestate succession by relatives are subject to the right of a bequeather's surviving spouse to the estate provided for in &sect; 16 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Esimese j&auml;rjekorra seadusj&auml;rgsed p&auml;rijad </eesti>
<inglise>First order intestate successors </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Esimese j&auml;rjekorra seadusj&auml;rgsed p&auml;rijad on p&auml;randaja alanejad sugulased. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) First order intestate successors are the descendants of a bequeather. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui p&auml;randaja surma ajal on elus p&auml;randaja alaneja sugulane, ei p&auml;ri selle sugulase alanejad sugulased, kes on p&auml;randajaga suguluses tema kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If at the time of death of a bequeather a descendant of the bequeather is alive, the descendants of that relative who are related to the bequeather through him or her shall not succeed. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Enne p&auml;randaja surma surnud alaneja sugulase asemele astuvad need alanejad sugulased, kes on p&auml;randajaga suguluses surnud alaneja kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A descendant who dies before the bequeather is replaced by the descendants who are related to the bequeather through the deceased descendant. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui p&auml;randaja ja p&auml;rija surid samal p&auml;eval ning ei ole v&otilde;imalik kindlaks teha, kumb neist suri varem, loetakse, et nad on surnud &uuml;hel ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a bequeather and successor die on the same day and it is not possible to determine which of them died earlier, they shall be deemed to have died at the same time. </inglise>
<eesti>Sel juhul ei p&auml;ri nad teineteise j&auml;rel ja kohaldamisele kuulub k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatu. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case, they do not succeed after one another and the provisions of subsection (3) of this section apply. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) P&auml;randaja lapsed p&auml;rivad v&otilde;rdsetes osades. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Children of a bequeather succeed in equal shares. </inglise>
<eesti>Surnud vanema asemele astunud lapsed p&auml;rivad v&otilde;rdsetes osades selle osa p&auml;randist, millele olnuks &otilde;igus nende surnud vanemal. </eesti>
<inglise>Children replacing a deceased parent succeed in equal shares to the share of the estate to which their deceased parent would have had the right. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>Teise j&auml;rjekorra seadusj&auml;rgsed p&auml;rijad </eesti>
<inglise>Second order intestate successors </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teise j&auml;rjekorra seadusj&auml;rgsed p&auml;rijad on p&auml;randaja vanemad ja nende alanejad sugulased. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Second order intestate successors are the parents of the bequeather and their descendants. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui p&auml;randi avanemise ajal on p&auml;randaja m&otilde;lemad vanemad elus, p&auml;rivad nad kogu p&auml;randi v&otilde;rdsetes osades. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If at the time of opening of a succession both parents of the bequeather are alive, they succeed to the entire estate in equal shares. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui p&auml;randi avanemise ajal p&auml;randaja isa v&otilde;i ema ei ole elus, astuvad surnud vanema asemele tema alanejad sugulased esimese j&auml;rjekorra p&auml;rijate kohta k&auml;ivate s&auml;tete j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If at the time of opening of a succession the father or mother of the bequeather is not alive, the descendants of the deceased parent replace him or her according to the provisions concerning first order successors. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui surnud vanemal alanejaid ei ole, p&auml;rib kogu p&auml;randi p&auml;randaja teine vanem. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If the deceased parent has no descendants, the other parent of the bequeather succeeds to the entire estate. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui ka teine vanem on surnud, p&auml;rivad tema alanejad sugulased esimese j&auml;rjekorra p&auml;rijate kohta k&auml;ivate s&auml;tete j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>If the other parent is also deceased, his or her descendants succeed according to the provisions concerning first order successors. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>Kolmanda j&auml;rjekorra seadusj&auml;rgsed p&auml;rijad </eesti>
<inglise>Third order intestate successors </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kolmanda j&auml;rjekorra seadusj&auml;rgsed p&auml;rijad on p&auml;randaja vanavanemad ja nende alanejad sugulased. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Third order intestate successors are the grandparents of the bequeather and their descendants. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui p&auml;randi avanemise ajal on elus k&otilde;ik vanavanemad, p&auml;rivad nad kogu p&auml;randi v&otilde;rdsetes osades. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If at the time of opening of a succession all the grandparents are alive, they succeed to the entire estate in equal shares. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui p&auml;randi avanemise ajaks on isa- v&otilde;i emapoolne vanavanem surnud, astuvad tema asemele tema alanejad. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If by the time of opening of a succession a paternal or maternal grandparent is deceased, his or her descendants replace him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui tal neid ei ole, p&auml;rib tema osa sama poole teine vanavanem. </eesti>
<inglise>If he or she has no descendants, the other grandparent on the same side succeeds to his or her share. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui ka teine vanavanem on surnud, p&auml;rivad tema alanejad. </eesti>
<inglise>If the other grandparent is also deceased, his or her descendants succeed. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui p&auml;randi avanemise ajaks on surnud m&otilde;lemad isa- v&otilde;i emapoolsed vanavanemad ning neil ei ole alanejaid sugulasi, p&auml;rivad teise poole vanavanemad v&otilde;i nende alanejad. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If by the time of opening of a succession both paternal or maternal grandparents are deceased and they have no descendants, the grandparents on the other side or their descendants succeed. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Alanejate astumisel oma vanemate asemele kohaldatakse esimese j&auml;rjekorra p&auml;rijate kohta k&auml;ivaid s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon replacement of parents by their descendants, the provisions concerning first order successors apply. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Abikaasa seadusj&auml;rgse p&auml;rijana </eesti>
<inglise>Spouse as intestate successor </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Koos p&auml;randaja sugulastega p&auml;rib p&auml;randaja &uuml;leelanud abikaasa seaduse j&auml;rgi: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Together with the relatives of a bequeather, the bequeather's surviving spouse succeeds in intestacy: </inglise>
<eesti>1) esimese j&auml;rjekorra p&auml;rijate k&otilde;rval v&otilde;rdselt p&auml;randaja lapse osaga, kuid mitte v&auml;hem kui &uuml;he neljandiku p&auml;randist; </eesti>
<inglise>1) with first order successors, equally with the share of a child of the bequeather but not to less than one-quarter of the estate; </inglise>
<eesti>2) teise j&auml;rjekorra p&auml;rijate k&otilde;rval poole p&auml;randist; </eesti>
<inglise>2) with second order successors, to one-half of the estate; </inglise>
<eesti>3) vanavanemate k&otilde;rval poole p&auml;randist, kui aga m&otilde;ni vanavanem on surnud, siis ka tema osa. </eesti>
<inglise>3) with grandparents, to one-half of the estate, but if any grandparent is deceased, also to his or her share. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui ei ole sugulasi esimesest ega teisest j&auml;rjekorrast ega vanavanemaid, p&auml;rib p&auml;randaja abikaasa kogu p&auml;randi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If there are no relatives from the first or second orders nor grandparents, the bequeather's spouse succeeds to the entire estate. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Abikaasa &otilde;igus eelosale </eesti>
<inglise>Right of spouse to preferential share </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui p&auml;randaja &uuml;leelanud abikaasa p&auml;rib koos teise j&auml;rjekorra p&auml;rijatega v&otilde;i p&auml;randaja vanavanematega, saab ta peale p&auml;randiosa eelosana abikaasade &uuml;hise kodu tavalise sisustuse esemed, kui need ei ole kinnisasja p&auml;raldised. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a bequeather's surviving spouse succeeds together with second order successors or grandparents of the bequeather, he or she receives in addition to a share of the estate the standard furnishings of the spouses' matrimonial home as a preferential share if the objects are not accessories of an immovable. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eelosa ei kuulu p&auml;randi hulka ja selle suhtes kohaldatakse annaku kohta k&auml;ivaid s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The preferential share does not form part of the estate and the provisions concerning a legacy apply thereto. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohaliku omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse ja riigi seadusj&auml;rgne p&auml;rimis&otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>Right of intestate succession of local government and state </inglise>
<eesti>Kui ei ole teisi p&auml;rijaid, on seadusj&auml;rgne p&auml;rija p&auml;randi avanemise koha kohalik omavalitsus&uuml;ksus. </eesti>
<inglise>The local government of the place of opening of a succession is the intestate successor if there are no other successors. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui p&auml;rand on avanenud v&auml;lismaal, on seadusj&auml;rgne p&auml;rija riik. </eesti>
<inglise>If a succession is opened abroad, the state is the intestate successor. </inglise>
<eesti>3. osa </eesti>
<inglise>Part 3 </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimine testamendi j&auml;rgi </eesti>
<inglise>Testate Succession </inglise>
<eesti>1. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 1 </inglise>
<eesti>Testament </eesti>
<inglise>Will </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Testamendi m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of will </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Testament on &uuml;hepoolne tehing, millega p&auml;randaja (testaator) teeb oma surma puhuks p&auml;randi kohta korraldusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A will is a unilateral transaction whereby a bequeather (testator) makes a disposition of his or her estate in the event of his or her death. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Testamendi teeb testaator isiklikult. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A testator shall make a will himself or herself. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>Testamendi liigid </eesti>
<inglise>Classification of wills </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Testament v&otilde;ib olla notariaalne v&otilde;i kodune. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A will may be notarial or domestic. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Notariaalne testament v&otilde;ib olla notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud v&otilde;i notari hoiule antud testament. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A notarial will may be a notarised will or a will deposited with a notary. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kodune testament v&otilde;ib olla tunnistajate juuresolekul alla kirjutatud v&otilde;i omak&auml;eliselt kirjutatud testament. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A domestic will may be a will signed in the presence of witnesses or a holographic will. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud testament </eesti>
<inglise>Notarised will </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Notar t&otilde;estab testamendi, mille ta on koostanud testaatori tahteavalduse kohaselt v&otilde;i mille on talle t&otilde;estamiseks esitanud testaator. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A notary shall attest a will which he or she has prepared according to the testamentary disposition of the testator or which a testator has submitted to him or her for attestation. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Testamendile kirjutab testaator alla notari juuresolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A testator shall sign his or her will in the presence of a notary. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui testaator f&uuml;&uuml;silise puude v&otilde;i haiguse t&otilde;ttu v&otilde;i muul p&otilde;hjusel ei ole v&otilde;imeline testamendile alla kirjutama, teeb seda tema &uuml;lesandel ning tema ja notari juuresolekul teine isik - aseallakirjutaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a testator is unable to sign his or her will due to a physical disability, illness or other reason, it shall be done with the authority of the testator and in the presence of the testator and a notary by another person, a deputy signatory. </inglise>
<eesti>Sel juhul m&auml;rgitakse testamendis p&otilde;hjus, miks testaator ei saa testamendile alla kirjutada. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case, the reason why the testator is unable to sign the will shall be noted in the will. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Aseallakirjutajaks ei v&otilde;i olla notar, tema &uuml;leneja ega alaneja sugulane, notari abikaasa ega abikaasa &uuml;leneja v&otilde;i alaneja sugulane, samuti notarib&uuml;roo t&ouml;&ouml;taja. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A notary, an ascendant or descendant of the notary, the notary's spouse, an ascendant or descendant of the spouse, or an employee of the notary's office shall not be a deputy signatory. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Notar ei v&otilde;i t&otilde;estada testamenti, kui see sisaldab korraldusi notari v&otilde;i tema &uuml;leneja v&otilde;i alaneja sugulase, notari abikaasa v&otilde;i abikaasa &uuml;leneja v&otilde;i alaneja sugulase, notari venna v&otilde;i &otilde;e v&otilde;i nende alaneja sugulase kasuks. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A notary shall not attest a will if it contains dispositions for the benefit of the notary or his or her ascendants or descendants, the notary's spouse or spouse's ascendants or descendants, or the notary's brother or sister or their descendants. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Notari hoiule antud testament </eesti>
<inglise>Will deposited with notary </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Testaator v&otilde;ib teha notariaalse testamendi sel teel, et annab isiklikult oma viimse tahte avalduse kinnises &uuml;mbrikus notari hoiule ning kinnitab notarile, et see on tema testament. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A testator may make a notarial will by depositing with a notary his or her will in a sealed envelope and confirming to the notary that it is his or her will. </inglise>
<eesti>Notar koostab testamendi hoiule andmise kohta dokumendi, millele kirjutavad alla testaator ja notar. </eesti>
<inglise>The notary shall prepare a document concerning the deposit of the will, which shall be signed by the testator and the notary. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Testaator v&otilde;ib notari hoiule antud testamendi igal ajal tagasi v&otilde;tta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A testator may retrieve his or her will deposited with a notary at any time. </inglise>
<eesti>Tagasiv&otilde;tmise kohta koostab notar dokumendi, millele kirjutavad alla testaator ja notar. </eesti>
<inglise>The notary shall prepare a document concerning the retrieval of the will, which shall be signed by the testator and the notary. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Tunnistajate juuresolekul allakirjutatud testament </eesti>
<inglise>Will signed in presence of witnesses </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Testaator v&otilde;ib teha koduse testamendi, millele ta kirjutab alla v&auml;hemalt kahe teov&otilde;imelise tunnistaja juuresolekul ning milles m&auml;rgib &auml;ra testamendi tegemise kuup&auml;eva ja aasta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A testator may make a domestic will, which he or she shall sign in the presence of at least two witnesses with active legal capacity and in which the testator shall indicate the date and year of making the will. </inglise>
<eesti>Tunnistajad peavad olema testamendi allakirjutamise juures &uuml;heaegselt. </eesti>
<inglise>The witnesses shall be present at the signing of the will concurrently. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tunnistajatele peab testaator teatama, et nad on kutsutud tunnistajateks testamendi tegemise juurde ning et testament sisaldab tema viimset tahet. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The testator shall notify the witnesses that they have been invited to witness the making of a will and that the will contains the testator's testamentary intention. </inglise>
<eesti>Ei ole n&otilde;utav, et tunnistajad teaksid testamendi sisu. </eesti>
<inglise>The witnesses are not required to know the content of the will. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kohe p&auml;rast seda, kui testaator on testamendile alla kirjutanud, kirjutavad sellele alla tunnistajad. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Immediately after the testator has signed his or her will, the witnesses shall sign it. </inglise>
<eesti>Tunnistajad kinnitavad oma allkirjaga, et testaator on testamendile ise alla kirjutanud ja et nende arusaamise kohaselt on testaator teo- ja otsustusv&otilde;imeline. </eesti>
<inglise>The witnesses confirm by their signature that the testator signed the will himself or herself and that according to their understanding the testator has active legal capacity and capacity to exercise will. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Tunnistajaks ei v&otilde;i olla isik, kelle enda v&otilde;i kelle &uuml;leneja v&otilde;i alaneja sugulase, venna v&otilde;i &otilde;e v&otilde;i nende alaneja sugulase v&otilde;i abikaasa v&otilde;i abikaasa &uuml;leneja v&otilde;i alaneja sugulase kasuks testament tehakse. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A person for whose own benefit or for the benefit of whose ascendant or descendant, brother or sister or their descendant, spouse or spouse's ascendant or descendant a will is made shall not be a witness. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui testamendi tegemisel on rikutud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 4 s&auml;testatud keeldu, on testamendis t&uuml;hised ainult need korraldused, mis on tehtud keeldu rikkudes. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If the prohibition provided for in subsection (4) of this section is violated in the making of a will, only the dispositions in the will which are made in violation of the prohibition are void. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Omak&auml;eliselt kirjutatud testament </eesti>
<inglise>Holographic will </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Testaator v&otilde;ib teha koduse testamendi, kirjutades selle algusest l&otilde;puni oma k&auml;ega ja m&auml;rkides &auml;ra testamendi tegemise kuup&auml;eva ja aasta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A testator may make a domestic will by writing it from beginning to end in his or her own handwriting and indicating the date and year of making the will. </inglise>
<eesti>Omak&auml;eliselt kirjutatud testamendile kirjutab testaator ise alla. </eesti>
<inglise>The testator shall sign his or her holographic will. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui omak&auml;eliselt kirjutatud testamendi on notar t&otilde;estanud, kehtib see notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud testamendina ning selle suhtes ei kohaldata k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 21 l&otilde;ikes 5 s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a notary attests a holographic will, it is valid as a notarised will and the provisions of subsection 21 (5) of this Act do not apply thereto. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui omak&auml;eliselt kirjutatud testamendile on alla kirjutanud ka tunnistajad, kehtib see omak&auml;eliselt kirjutatud testamendina ning selle suhtes ei kohaldata k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 23 l&otilde;igetes 4 ja 5 s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If witnesses also sign a holographic will, it is valid as a holographic will and the provisions of subsections 23 (4) and (5) of this Act do not apply thereto. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>Koduse testamendi kehtivuse aeg </eesti>
<inglise>Term of validity of domestic will </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kodune testament kaotab kehtivuse, kui selle tegemise p&auml;evast on m&ouml;&ouml;dunud kuus kuud ja testaator sel ajal elab. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A domestic will becomes invalid if six months have elapsed from the date of its making and the testator is alive at the time. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui koduses testamendis pole m&auml;rgitud selle tegemise kuup&auml;eva ega aastat ning ka muul viisil ei ole v&otilde;imalik tuvastada testamendi tegemise p&auml;eva, on testament t&uuml;hine. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a domestic will does not indicate the date and year of its making and it is not possible to establish the date of making the will in any other manner, the will is void. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>Koduse testamendi hoidmine </eesti>
<inglise>Safe-keeping of domestic will </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Testaator v&otilde;ib kodust testamenti hoida ise v&otilde;i anda hoidmiseks teisele isikule. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A testator may keep a domestic will himself or herself or give it to another person for safe-keeping. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Saanud teada testaatori surmast, on isik, kellele testaator on testamendi hoiule andnud v&otilde;i kelle valduses on testament muul alusel, kohustatud testamendi viivitamata esitama p&auml;randi avanemise koha notarile. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon becoming aware of the death of a testator, a person with whom the testator has deposited his or her will or who possesses the will on another basis is required to submit the will promptly to a notary of the place of opening of the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>Notar v&auml;ljastab koduse testamendi esitajale testamendi hoiule v&otilde;tmise kohta dokumendi, millele kirjutavad alla testamendi esitaja ja notar. </eesti>
<inglise>The notary shall issue the person who submits a domestic will a document concerning the deposit of the will and the document shall be signed by the person who submits the will and the notary. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.99 j&otilde;ust.31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 t&auml;hendatud isik on s&uuml;&uuml;liselt testamendi k&otilde;rvaldanud v&otilde;i seda varjanud, on p&auml;randist huvitatud isikul &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda s&uuml;&uuml;dlaselt p&auml;randi selle osa h&uuml;vitamist, mis tal j&auml;i teistelt p&auml;rijatelt saamata. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the person referred to in subsection (2) of this section wrongfully removes or conceals the will, a person who has an interest in the estate has the right to demand compensation from the offender for the share of the estate which the person failed to receive from the other successors. </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Testamendi sisu </eesti>
<inglise>Content of Will </inglise>
<eesti>1. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 1 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>Testamendi t&otilde;lgendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Interpretation of will </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Testamendi t&otilde;lgendamisel l&auml;htutakse selles kasutatud s&otilde;nade &uuml;ldlevinud t&auml;hendusest, kui testaator ei ole neile andnud teist t&auml;hendust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The interpretation of a will shall be based on the ordinary meaning of the words used therein unless the testator has given them a different meaning. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Testamendis leiduvate segaste, kahem&otilde;tteliste v&otilde;i oskamatult s&otilde;nastatud v&auml;ljendite t&otilde;lgendamisel arvestatakse testaatori kirjalikke v&otilde;i teistele isikutele antud selgitusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the interpretation of ambiguous, equivocal or incomprehensible expressions in a will, the statements of the testator, written or given to other persons, shall be considered. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui testamendi m&otilde;nda korraldust saab t&otilde;lgendada mitut moodi ning ei ole alust neist &uuml;hte eelistada, eelistatakse t&otilde;lgendust, mille kohaselt testament j&auml;&auml;b kehtima v&otilde;imalikult suuremas ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If any disposition in a will can be interpreted in several ways and there is no reason to prefer one of them, the interpretation according to which the will remains valid to the greatest possible extent shall be preferred. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Arusaamatu korraldus loetakse olematuks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An incomprehensible disposition shall be deemed to be non-existent. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>Isikute ja asjade nimetamine testamendis </eesti>
<inglise>Specification of persons and things in will </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isikute ja asjade nimetamisel testamendis piisab seesugusest nimetamisest v&otilde;i kirjeldamisest, mis ei j&auml;ta testaatori tahtes kahtlust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In the specification of persons and things in a will, a specification or description which leaves no doubt as to the intention of the testator is sufficient. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui testaatori tahtes kahtlust ei ole, ei m&otilde;juta testamendi kehtivust eksimus asjade v&otilde;i isikute nimetamises v&otilde;i kirjeldamises ega see, et isiku v&otilde;i asja testamendis nimetatud omadus v&otilde;i tunnus on hiljem kadunud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If there is no doubt as to the intention of the testator, the validity of a will is not affected by an error in a specification or description of things or persons or that a characteristic or trait of a person or thing specified in the will is later lost. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>Testament teatud isikuteringi kasuks </eesti>
<inglise>Will for benefit of particular group of persons </inglise>
<eesti>Kui testaator on testamendis teinud korralduse teatud isikuteringi kasuks isikuid t&auml;pselt m&auml;&auml;ramata, loetakse korraldus tehtuks k&otilde;igi nende kasuks, kes p&auml;randi avanemise ajal kuulusid testamendis n&auml;idatud isikuteringi, kui testamendist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>If a testator makes a disposition in a will for the benefit of a particular group of persons without specifying the persons exactly, the disposition shall be deemed to be made for the benefit of all those who belong to the group of persons specified in the will at the time of opening of the succession unless otherwise provided by the will. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>Testament alaneja sugulase kasuks, kes p&auml;rast testamendi tegemist sureb </eesti>
<inglise>Will for benefit of descendant who dies after making of will </inglise>
<eesti>Kui testaator on testamendis teinud korralduse alaneja sugulase kasuks, kes p&auml;rast testamendi tegemist, kuid enne p&auml;randi avanemist sureb, j&auml;ttes j&auml;rele alanejad sugulased, loetakse korraldus tehtuks ka alanejate sugulaste kasuks selle p&auml;randiosa ulatuses, mille nad saaksid surnud alaneja sugulase asemele astumise korral seadusj&auml;rgselt p&auml;rides, kui testamendist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>If a testator makes a disposition in a will for the benefit of a descendant who dies after the making of the will but before the opening of the succession, leaving descendants, the disposition shall be deemed to be made also for the benefit of the descendants to the extent of the share of the estate which they would receive by intestate succession upon replacing the deceased descendant, unless otherwise provided by the will. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 31. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 31. </inglise>
<eesti>Korraldus kasutada p&auml;randit heategevuseks </eesti>
<inglise>Disposition to use estate for charity </inglise>
<eesti>Kui testaator on testamendis teinud korralduse kasutada p&auml;randit v&otilde;i selle osa heategevuseks t&auml;psemat korraldust tegemata, loetakse korraldus tehtuks testaatori viimase elukoha kohaliku omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse kasuks kohustusega kasutada p&auml;randit v&otilde;i selle osa heategevuseks. </eesti>
<inglise>If a testator makes a disposition in a will to use the estate or a share thereof for charity without making a more exact disposition, the disposition shall be deemed to be made for the benefit of the local government of the last residence of the testator with the obligation to use the estate or the share thereof for charity. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 32. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 32. </inglise>
<eesti>Isiku kirjeldamine testamendis </eesti>
<inglise>Description of person in will </inglise>
<eesti>Kui testaator on testamendis teinud korralduse isiku kasuks, keda ta on kirjeldanud mitme isiku kohta k&auml;ival viisil, ning ei ole selge, keda on silmas peetud, loetakse korraldus tehtuks k&otilde;igi nende isikute kasuks v&otilde;rdsetes osades. </eesti>
<inglise>If a testator makes a disposition in a will for the benefit of a person who he or she describes in a manner which applies to several persons and it is unclear who is meant, the disposition shall be deemed to be made for the benefit of all the persons in equal shares. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 33. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 33. </inglise>
<eesti>Tingimusega korraldus </eesti>
<inglise>Conditional disposition </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Testaator v&otilde;ib testamendis p&auml;rija nimetada v&otilde;i annaku m&auml;&auml;rata edasil&uuml;kkava tingimusega v&otilde;i t&auml;htaja m&auml;&auml;ramisega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A testator may nominate a successor or give a legacy with a suspensive condition or specified term in a will. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Testaator v&otilde;ib testamendis teha ka muid edasil&uuml;kkava v&otilde;i &auml;ramuutva tingimusega v&otilde;i m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htajaga korraldusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A testator may also make other dispositions with a suspensive or resolutive condition or with a specified term in a will. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34. </inglise>
<eesti>Tingimus annakut saavale p&auml;rijale </eesti>
<inglise>Condition on successor receiving legacy </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui p&auml;rija on nimetatud tingimusega (&sect; 33 lg. 1) ning p&auml;rijale on testamendis m&auml;&auml;ratud ka annak, kehtib tingimus ka annaku suhtes, kui testamendist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a successor is nominated with a condition (&sect; 33 (1)) and a legacy is also given to the successor in a will, the condition is also valid with respect to the legacy unless otherwise provided by the will. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui annak on p&auml;rijale m&auml;&auml;ratud tingimusega (&sect; 33 lg. 1), ei s&otilde;ltu annakusaaja p&auml;rijaks olek sellest tingimusest, kui testamendist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a legacy is given to a successor with a condition (&sect; 33 (1)), the legatee's capacity as a successor is not dependent on the condition unless otherwise provided by the will. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>Edasil&uuml;kkava tingimusega korraldus </eesti>
<inglise>Disposition with suspensive condition </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui testaator on testamendis teinud edasil&uuml;kkava tingimusega korralduse, kehtib korraldus ainult siis, kui isik, kelle kasuks korraldus on tehtud, on tingimuse saabumisel elus, kui testamendist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a testator makes a disposition with a suspensive condition in a will, the disposition is valid only if the person for whose benefit the disposition is made is alive upon fulfilment of the condition unless otherwise provided by the will. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Edasil&uuml;kkava tingimusega p&auml;rijaks nimetatud isikule v&otilde;idakse p&auml;randi avanemisel p&auml;rand &uuml;le anda ka enne selle tingimuse saabumist, kui ta annab k&uuml;llaldase tagatise sellele isikule, kellele ta peaks p&auml;randi loovutama, kui tingimus ei saabu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon the opening of a succession, a person nominated as a successor with a suspensive condition may have the estate transferred to the person before fulfilment of the condition if the person provides adequate security to the person to whom the person must surrender the estate if the condition is not fulfilled. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 36. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 36. </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;iendav korraldus </eesti>
<inglise>Supplementary disposition </inglise>
<eesti>Kui testaator on testamendis v&auml;ljendanud tahet teha edaspidi t&auml;iendavaid korraldusi, kuid ei ole neid teinud, on testament kehtiv, kui testaator ei ole testamendi kehtivust teinud s&otilde;ltuvaks nendest korraldustest. </eesti>
<inglise>If a testator expresses in a will an intention to make supplementary dispositions in the future but has not made them, the will is valid unless the testator makes the validity of the will dependent on these dispositions. </inglise>
<eesti>2. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Testamendij&auml;rgne p&auml;rija </eesti>
<inglise>Testate Successor </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 37. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 37. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rija nimetamine </eesti>
<inglise>Nomination of successor </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Testamendij&auml;rgne p&auml;rija on isik, kellele testaator on testamendiga p&auml;randanud kogu oma vara v&otilde;i m&otilde;ttelise osa (murdosa) sellest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A testate successor is a person to whom a testator bequeaths by a will all his or her property or a legal share (fraction) thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui testament k&auml;ib p&auml;randi osa kohta, p&auml;ritakse p&auml;randi &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;nud osa seaduse j&auml;rgi, kui selle osa kohta ei ole s&otilde;lmitud p&auml;rimislepingut. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a will concerns a share of an estate, the residual share of the estate is succeeded to in intestacy unless a testamentary contract is entered into concerning that share. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui testaator on testamendis nimetanud oma ainukesed p&auml;rijad, kuid neile j&auml;etud p&auml;randiosad kokku ei moodusta kogu p&auml;randit, suurendatakse iga&uuml;he p&auml;randiosa v&otilde;rdeliselt testamendis m&auml;&auml;ratud osa suurusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a testator nominates his or her successors in a will, but the shares of the estate left to them total less than the entire estate, everyone's share of the estate shall be increased in proportion to the size of the share specified in the will. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui testamendis nimetatud p&auml;rijatele j&auml;etud p&auml;randiosad kokku on suuremad kogu p&auml;randist, v&auml;hendatakse iga&uuml;he p&auml;randiosa v&otilde;rdeliselt testamendis m&auml;&auml;ratud osa suurusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If the shares of an estate left to the successors nominated in a will total more than the entire estate, everyone's share of the estate shall be decreased in proportion to the size of his or her share specified in the will. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 38. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 38. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rijate nimetamine p&auml;randiosi m&auml;&auml;ramata </eesti>
<inglise>Nomination of successors without specification of shares of estate </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui testamendis nimetatud p&auml;rijate p&auml;randiosad on m&auml;&auml;ramata, loetakse nende p&auml;randiosad v&otilde;rdseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If the shares of an estate of the successors nominated in a will are unspecified, their shares of the estate shall be deemed to be equal. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui testamendis on nimetatud mitu p&auml;rijat, kellest m&otilde;ne p&auml;randiosa on m&auml;&auml;ratud, p&auml;rivad need p&auml;rijad, kelle osa on m&auml;&auml;ramata, p&auml;randiosadega h&otilde;lmamata osa p&auml;randist v&otilde;rdsetes osades. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If several successors are nominated in a will some of whose shares of the estate are specified, those successors whose shares are unspecified succeed in equal shares to the part of the estate not included in shares of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud p&auml;randiosad kokku moodustavad terviku v&otilde;i &uuml;letavad selle, v&auml;hendatakse v&otilde;rdeliselt k&otilde;iki p&auml;randiosi sel m&auml;&auml;ral, et p&auml;rija, kelle osa ei ole m&auml;&auml;ratud, saaks p&auml;randist sama suure osa kui p&auml;rija, kes saab k&otilde;ige v&auml;iksema osa. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the shares of the estate specified in subsection (2) of this section together form the whole or exceed it, all shares of the estate are decreased in proportion so that the successors whose shares are not specified receive as large a share of the estate as the successor who receives the smallest share. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui testamendis on nimetatud p&auml;rijateks sugulased nende isikuid ja p&auml;randiosi m&auml;&auml;ramata, toimub p&auml;rimine samas korras nagu seadusj&auml;rgne p&auml;rimine. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If relatives are nominated in a will as successors without specifying their identities and shares of the estate, the succession is effected pursuant to the same procedure as intestate succession. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 39. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 39. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;he p&auml;randiosa p&auml;rijad </eesti>
<inglise>Successors of one share of estate </inglise>
<eesti>Kui p&auml;rijate hulgast m&otilde;ned on nimetatud &uuml;he ja sama p&auml;randiosa saajaks, kohaldatakse selle &uuml;hise p&auml;randiosa suhtes p&auml;randi kui terviku kohta k&auml;ivaid s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>If from among successors some are nominated as recipients of one and the same share of an estate, the provisions concerning an estate as a whole apply to this joint share of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>3. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 3 </inglise>
<eesti>Asep&auml;rija </eesti>
<inglise>Alternative Successor </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 40. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 40. </inglise>
<eesti>Asep&auml;rija nimetamine </eesti>
<inglise>Nomination of alternative successor </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Testaator v&otilde;ib nimetada p&auml;rija asemele &uuml;he v&otilde;i mitu asep&auml;rijat juhuks, kui p&auml;rijaks nimetatud isik sureb enne p&auml;randi avanemist, loobub p&auml;randist, ei v&otilde;ta p&auml;randit vastu v&otilde;i on p&auml;rimisk&otilde;lbmatu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A testator may nominate one or several alternative successors in place of a successor if a person nominated as a successor dies before the opening of the succession, renounces the succession, does not accept the succession or is unworthy to succeed. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui testamendist ei n&auml;htu, milliseks k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud juhuks on asep&auml;rija nimetatud, loetakse, et asep&auml;rija on nimetatud k&otilde;ikideks nendeks juhtudeks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If it is not evident from a will in which of the cases specified in subsection (1) of this section an alternative successor is nominated, the alternative successor shall be deemed to be nominated in all the cases. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Asep&auml;rijaid nimetades v&otilde;ib testaator m&auml;&auml;rata, millises j&auml;rjekorras asep&auml;rijad p&auml;rijaks saavad. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In nominating alternative successors, a testator may specify in which order the alternative successors become successors. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 41. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 41. </inglise>
<eesti>Asep&auml;rija p&auml;rijaks saamine </eesti>
<inglise>Alternative successor becoming successor </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Asep&auml;rija saab p&auml;rijaks, kui saabub tingimus, mille puhuks ta oli nimetatud (&sect; 40). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An alternative successor becomes a successor if the condition on which the alternative successor was nominated (&sect; 40) is fulfilled. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teine ja j&auml;rgnevad asep&auml;rijad ei kaota &otilde;igust p&auml;rida, kui neile eelnev asep&auml;rija sureb enne p&auml;rijat v&otilde;i j&auml;rjekorras eelnevat asep&auml;rijat. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Second and subsequent alternative successors do not lose the right to succeed if the alternative successor preceding them dies before the successor or the alternative successor preceding in order. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 42. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 42. </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;relp&auml;rija asep&auml;rijana </eesti>
<inglise>Subsequent successor as alternative successor </inglise>
<eesti>(1) J&auml;relp&auml;rijat loetakse ka asep&auml;rijaks, kui testamendist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A subsequent successor shall also be deemed to be an alternative successor unless otherwise provided by the will. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui testamendist ei n&auml;htu, kas isik on nimetatud asep&auml;rijaks v&otilde;i j&auml;relp&auml;rijaks, loetakse ta asep&auml;rijaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If it is not evident from a will whether a person is nominated as an alternative successor or a subsequent successor, the person shall be deemed to be an alternative successor. </inglise>
<eesti>4. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 4 </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;relp&auml;rija </eesti>
<inglise>Subsequent Successor </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 43. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 43. </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;relp&auml;rija nimetamine </eesti>
<inglise>Nomination of subsequent successor </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Testaator v&otilde;ib testamendis m&auml;&auml;rata, et teatava t&auml;htp&auml;eva v&otilde;i edasil&uuml;kkava tingimuse saabumise korral l&auml;heb kogu p&auml;rand v&otilde;i osa sellest &uuml;le p&auml;rijalt j&auml;relp&auml;rijale. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A testator may provide in a will that in the case of arrival of a particular date or fulfilment of a suspensive condition the entire estate or a share thereof transfers from a successor to a subsequent successor. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rija, kellele on nimetatud j&auml;relp&auml;rija, on eelp&auml;rija. </eesti>
<inglise>A successor for whom a subsequent successor is nominated is a provisional successor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) J&auml;relp&auml;rijale ei saa m&auml;&auml;rata j&auml;relp&auml;rijat. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A subsequent successor cannot be designated for a subsequent successor. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui testaator on m&auml;&auml;ranud, et p&auml;rijaks nimetatud isik saab p&auml;randi k&auml;tte teatava t&auml;htp&auml;eva v&otilde;i edasil&uuml;kkava tingimuse saabumisel, kuid ei ole m&auml;&auml;ranud eelp&auml;rijat, on eelp&auml;rijateks p&auml;randaja seadusj&auml;rgsed p&auml;rijad. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a testator provides that a person nominated as a successor receives the estate on a particular date or upon fulfilment of a suspensive condition, but has not nominated a provisional successor, the intestate successors of the testator are the provisional successors. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui testaator on nimetanud p&auml;rijaks f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku, kes eostatakse ja s&uuml;nnib p&auml;rast p&auml;randi avanemist, v&otilde;i juriidilise isiku, mis luuakse p&auml;rast p&auml;randi avanemist, loetakse ta j&auml;relp&auml;rijaks, kui testamendist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a testator nominates a natural person who is conceived and born after the opening of the succession or a legal person which is established after the opening of the succession as a successor, the person shall be deemed to be a subsequent successor unless otherwise provided by the will. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 44. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 44. </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;relp&auml;rija nimetamine t&auml;htp&auml;eva v&otilde;i tingimust m&auml;&auml;ramata </eesti>
<inglise>Nomination of subsequent successor without specification of date or condition </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui testaator on j&auml;relp&auml;rija nimetanud t&auml;htp&auml;eva v&otilde;i edasil&uuml;kkavat tingimust m&auml;&auml;ramata, p&auml;rib j&auml;relp&auml;rija eelp&auml;rija surma korral. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a testator nominates a subsequent successor without specifying a due date or suspensive condition, the subsequent successor shall succeed upon the death of the provisional successor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui j&auml;relp&auml;rijaks on nimetatud isik, kes p&auml;randi avanemise ajaks ei ole veel s&uuml;ndinud, saab ta s&uuml;ndimise korral j&auml;relp&auml;rijaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a person who is not born by the time of opening of a succession is nominated as a subsequent successor, he or she shall become a subsequent successor upon birth. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui j&auml;relp&auml;rijaks on nimetatud p&auml;randi avanemise ajaks veel asutamata juriidiline isik, saab see asutamise korral j&auml;relp&auml;rijaks. </eesti>
<inglise>If a legal person not yet established by the time of opening of a succession is nominated as a subsequent successor, the legal person shall become a subsequent successor upon establishment. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui j&auml;relp&auml;rijaks nimetatud f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik ei ole s&uuml;ndinud v&otilde;i juriidiline isik ei ole asutatud 30 aasta jooksul p&auml;randi avanemisest, kaotab j&auml;relp&auml;rijaks nimetamine kehtivuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a natural person nominated as a subsequent successor is not born or a legal person nominated as a subsequent successor is not established within thirty years after the opening of the succession, the nomination of the subsequent successor becomes invalid. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 45. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 45. </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;relp&auml;rija surm </eesti>
<inglise>Death of subsequent successor </inglise>
<eesti>Kui j&auml;relp&auml;rija sureb p&auml;rast p&auml;randi avanemist, kuid enne j&auml;relp&auml;rimise t&auml;htp&auml;eva saabumist, l&auml;heb tema p&auml;rimis&otilde;igus &uuml;le tema p&auml;rijatele, kui testamendist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>If a subsequent successor dies after the opening of the succession but before the date of the subsequent succession, his or her right of succession transfers to his or her successors unless otherwise provided by the will. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 46. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 46. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randi v&otilde;&otilde;randamine v&otilde;i koormamine </eesti>
<inglise>Transfer or encumbrance of estate </inglise>
<eesti>Eelp&auml;rija v&otilde;ib p&auml;randit v&otilde;&otilde;randada v&otilde;i koormata, kui see on temale lubatud testamendiga v&otilde;i seda on lubanud j&auml;relp&auml;rija v&otilde;i kui seda on vaja annaku t&auml;itmiseks v&otilde;i testaatori nende v&otilde;lgade tasumiseks, mille tasumise t&auml;htp&auml;ev on saabunud. </eesti>
<inglise>A provisional successor may transfer or encumber the estate if the provisional successor is so authorised by the will or by the subsequent successor or if this is required for execution of a legacy or for payment of the testator's debts the date for payment of which has arrived. </inglise>
<eesti>Eelp&auml;rija v&otilde;ib m&uuml;&uuml;a kiiresti riknevaid asju ja asju, mille otstarbekohane tarvitamine seisneb nende v&otilde;&otilde;randamises. </eesti>
<inglise>A provisional successor may sell highly perishable things and things whose intended use involves their transfer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 47. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 47. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randi s&auml;ilitamise kulutused </eesti>
<inglise>Expenses for preservation of estate </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Eelp&auml;rija v&otilde;ib p&auml;randi arvel teha selle s&auml;ilitamiseks vajalikke kulutusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A provisional successor may incur expenses necessary for preservation of the estate out of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui ta on need teinud oma arvel, peab p&auml;randi saanud j&auml;relp&auml;rija kulutused eelp&auml;rijale h&uuml;vitama. </eesti>
<inglise>If the provisional successor has incurred these at the provisional successor's own expense, the subsequent successor who receives the estate shall reimburse the expenses to the provisional successor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&auml;randiga seotud kasulike ja toreduslike kulutuste h&uuml;vitamisel kohaldatakse asja&otilde;igusseaduse (RT I 1993, 39, 590; 1995, 26-28, 355; 57, 976) &sect;-des 28 ja 29 s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon reimbursement of useful and sumptuary expenses relating to an estate, the provisions of &sect;&sect; 28 and 29 of the Law on Property Act (RT I 1993, 39, 590; 1995, 26-28, 355; 57, 976) apply. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 48. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 48. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randvara nimekiri </eesti>
<inglise>Inventory of estate </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Eelp&auml;rija peab j&auml;relp&auml;rija n&otilde;udmisel andma talle p&auml;randvara nimekirja, millele eelp&auml;rija on alla kirjutanud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) At the request of a subsequent successor, a provisional successor shall provide the subsequent successor with an inventory of the estate which is signed by the provisional successor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) J&auml;relp&auml;rija v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda, et teda kutsutakse p&auml;randvara nimekirja koostamise juurde. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A subsequent successor may demand that the subsequent successor be invited to the preparation of an inventory of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) P&auml;randvara nimekirja koostamise kulud kaetakse p&auml;randi arvel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The expenditure for preparation of the inventory of an estate is recoverable from the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 49. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 49. </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;relp&auml;rija &otilde;iguste tagamine </eesti>
<inglise>Guarantee of rights of subsequent successor </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui eelp&auml;rija tegevuse v&otilde;i tema varalise seisundi t&otilde;ttu tekib j&auml;relp&auml;rijal p&otilde;hjendatud kahtlus, et tema &otilde;igusi v&otilde;idakse rikkuda, v&otilde;ib ta n&otilde;uda, et eelp&auml;rija tema &otilde;igused tagaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If due to the activity or financial situation of a provisional successor a subsequent successor has good reason to suspect that the subsequent successor's rights may be prejudiced, the subsequent successor may demand that the provisional successor guarantee the subsequent successor's rights. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui eelp&auml;rija seda ei tee, v&otilde;ib j&auml;relp&auml;rija oma &otilde;iguste tagamist taotleda kohtu kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise>If the provisional successor fails to do so, the subsequent successor may apply for the guarantee of the subsequent successor's rights by a court proceeding. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) J&auml;relp&auml;rija taotluse alusel v&otilde;ib kohus anda eelp&auml;rijale n&otilde;ude tagamise t&auml;htaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The court may grant to the provisional successor a term for securing the claim on the basis of the application of the subsequent successor. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui eelp&auml;rija ei ole t&auml;htaja jooksul j&auml;relp&auml;rija &otilde;igusi taganud, antakse j&auml;relp&auml;rija n&otilde;udel p&auml;rand valitseda kohtu m&auml;&auml;ratud hooldajale, kelle &otilde;igused p&auml;randit k&auml;sutada on piiratud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 46 s&auml;testatuga. </eesti>
<inglise>If the provisional successor does not guarantee the rights of the subsequent successor within the term, the estate shall at the request of the subsequent successor be transferred to the management of a court-appointed administrator whose right to dispose of the estate is restricted by the provisions of &sect; 46 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui eelp&auml;rija annab piisava tagatise, v&otilde;ib ta n&otilde;uda, et p&auml;randi valitsemine antakse p&auml;randihooldajalt temale &uuml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the provisional successor provides sufficient security, the provisional successor may demand that the administration of the estate be transferred from the administrator of the estate to the provisional successor. </inglise>
<eesti>Sel juhul peab p&auml;randi hooldaja eelp&auml;rijale &uuml;le andma ka p&auml;randist saadud tulu, millest on maha arvatud p&auml;randi valitsemise kulud. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case, the administrator of the estate shall also transfer to the provisional successor the income received from the estate from which the expenditure for administration of the estate has been deducted. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 50. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 50. </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;relp&auml;rijale &uuml;leminev p&auml;rand </eesti>
<inglise>Estate to be transferred to subsequent successor </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui p&auml;rimis&otilde;igus l&auml;heb &uuml;le j&auml;relp&auml;rijale, on eelp&auml;rija kohustatud p&auml;randvara &uuml;le andma. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If the right of succession transfers to a subsequent successor, the provisional successor is required to transfer the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randvara tuleb &uuml;le anda sellises seisukorras, nagu see peaks olema &uuml;leandmiseni kestnud heaperemeheliku valitsemise korral. </eesti>
<inglise>The estate shall be transferred in the condition it would be if it had been prudently managed until the transfer. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) J&auml;relp&auml;rijale &uuml;lemineva p&auml;randi hulka kuulub vara, mille eelp&auml;rija on omandanud p&auml;randisse kuuluva &otilde;iguse alusel v&otilde;i p&auml;randi arvel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Property which a provisional successor acquires on the basis of rights belonging to the estate or out of the estate forms part of the estate to be transferred to a subsequent successor. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) J&auml;relp&auml;rijale &uuml;lemineva p&auml;randi hulka ei arvata vara, mille eelp&auml;rija on &auml;ra tarvitanud oma oludele vastava tavalise tarbimise piires. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Property which a provisional successor has consumed within the limits of regular use according to the provisional successor's circumstances is not included as part of the estate to be transferred to a subsequent successor. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) J&auml;relp&auml;rimise &otilde;iguse tekkimiseni p&auml;randist saadud vili kuulub eelp&auml;rijale. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Fruit received from an estate until creation of the right of subsequent succession belongs to the provisional successor. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Eelp&auml;rija peab j&auml;relp&auml;rija n&otilde;udel esitama talle p&auml;randi valitsemise aruande. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) At the request of a subsequent successor, the provisional successor shall present a report on the administration of the estate to the subsequent successor. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 51. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 51. </inglise>
<eesti>Eelp&auml;rija vastutus p&auml;randvara v&auml;&auml;rtuse v&auml;henemise eest </eesti>
<inglise>Liability of provisional successor for decrease in value of estate </inglise>
<eesti>Eelp&auml;rija ei vastuta j&auml;relp&auml;rija ees p&auml;randvara v&auml;&auml;rtuse v&auml;henemise eest, kui ta on vara heaperemehelikult valitsenud. </eesti>
<inglise>A provisional successor is not liable to a subsequent successor for a decrease in the value of the estate if the provisional successor has managed the estate prudently. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 52. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 52. </inglise>
<eesti>Eelp&auml;rija vabastamine kitsendustest ja kohustustest </eesti>
<inglise>Exemption of provisional successor from restrictions and obligations </inglise>
<eesti>Kui testaator on testamendis m&auml;&auml;ranud, et j&auml;relp&auml;rijale l&auml;heb p&auml;randist &uuml;le &uuml;ksnes see, mis j&auml;relp&auml;rimise &otilde;iguse tekkimise ajaks on p&auml;randist j&auml;rele j&auml;&auml;nud, v&otilde;i kui testamendis on ette n&auml;htud eelp&auml;rija &otilde;igus p&auml;randit vabalt k&auml;sutada, loetakse eelp&auml;rija seaduses s&auml;testatud kitsendustest ja kohustustest vabastatuks. </eesti>
<inglise>If a testator has provided in a will that only that which remains of the estate by the time the right of subsequent succession arises transfers to a subsequent successor, or if the will provides the right of a provisional successor to dispose of the estate freely, the provisional successor shall be deemed to be exempt from the restrictions and obligations provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 53. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 53. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;igussuhted j&auml;relp&auml;rimisel </eesti>
<inglise>Legal relations upon subsequent succession </inglise>
<eesti>(1) J&auml;relp&auml;rimise &otilde;iguse tekkimisest alates ei ole eelp&auml;rija enam p&auml;rija ning j&auml;relp&auml;rijal on &otilde;igus p&auml;rand vastu v&otilde;tta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) After the right of subsequent succession arises, a provisional successor is no longer the successor and a subsequent successor has the right to accept the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tmisega l&auml;hevad p&auml;rija &otilde;igused ja kohustused &uuml;le j&auml;relp&auml;rijale. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The rights and obligations of a successor transfer to a subsequent successor with acceptance of the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui j&auml;relp&auml;rija p&auml;randit vastu ei v&otilde;ta v&otilde;i p&auml;rimisk&otilde;lbmatuse t&otilde;ttu vastu v&otilde;tta ei saa, j&auml;&auml;b p&auml;rand eelp&auml;rijale, kui testamendist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a subsequent successor does not accept a succession or cannot accept it due to unworthiness to succeed, the estate remains with the provisional successor unless otherwise provided by the will. </inglise>
<eesti>5. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Annak </eesti>
<inglise>Legacy </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 54. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 54. </inglise>
<eesti>Annaku m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of legacy </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui testaator ei ole testamendis isikule m&auml;&auml;ranud kogu oma vara v&otilde;i selle m&otilde;ttelist osa, vaid teatud varalise h&uuml;ve, loetakse see annakuks ja h&uuml;ve saaja annakusaajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If in a will a testator does not give all his or her property or a legal share thereof to a person but gives a particular proprietary benefit, it shall be deemed to be a legacy and the recipient of the benefit shall be deemed to be a legatee. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud varaline h&uuml;ve v&otilde;ib olla asi, rahasumma, samuti &otilde;igus v&otilde;i kohustusest vabastamine. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A proprietary benefit specified in subsection (1) of this section may be a thing, sum of money, right or exemption from an obligation. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Testaator v&otilde;ib teha annaku m&auml;&auml;ramise kohustuseks p&auml;rijale v&otilde;i teisele annakusaajale. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A testator may make the giving of a legacy an obligation of a successor or another legatee. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 55. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 55. </inglise>
<eesti>Annakusaaja p&auml;rimisv&otilde;ime </eesti>
<inglise>Succession capacity of legatee </inglise>
<eesti>Annaku v&otilde;ib saada isik, kes on annakule &otilde;iguse tekkimise ajal p&auml;rimisv&otilde;imeline ega ole p&auml;rimisk&otilde;lbmatu. </eesti>
<inglise>A person who has succession capacity and is not unworthy to succeed at the time the right to a legacy arises may receive the legacy. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 56. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 56. </inglise>
<eesti>Annakut&auml;itja </eesti>
<inglise>Executor of legacy </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Testaator v&otilde;ib annaku t&auml;itmise teha kohustuseks p&auml;rijale v&otilde;i teisele annakusaajale (annakut&auml;itjad). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A testator may make execution of a legacy an obligation of a successor or another legatee (executor of legacy). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui annakut&auml;itja on surnud, ei ole p&auml;randit v&otilde;i annakut vastu v&otilde;tnud v&otilde;i on p&auml;rimisk&otilde;lbmatu, l&auml;heb annaku t&auml;itmise kohustus &uuml;le isikule, kes astub tema asemele ja on v&otilde;imeline annakut t&auml;itma. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the executor of a legacy is deceased, does not accept the succession or legacy or is unworthy to succeed, the obligation to execute the legacy transfers to a person who replaces the executor of the legacy and is capable of executing a legacy. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 nimetatud isikuid ei ole, korraldab annaku t&auml;itmist testamendit&auml;itja. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If there are no persons specified in subsections (1) and (2) of this section, the executor of the will shall arrange for execution of the legacy. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 57. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 57. </inglise>
<eesti>Annaku t&auml;itmise ulatus </eesti>
<inglise>Extent of execution of legacy </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Annakut t&auml;itev p&auml;rija v&otilde;i teine annakusaaja on kohustatud annakut t&auml;itma p&auml;randist saadud vara ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A successor or another legatee who executes a legacy is required to execute the legacy to the extent of the property received from the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui p&auml;randist k&otilde;igi annakute t&auml;itmiseks ei piisa, v&auml;hendatakse annakuid v&otilde;rdeliselt nende suurusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If an estate is insufficient for execution of all legacies, the legacies are reduced in proportion to their size. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 58. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 58. </inglise>
<eesti>Annakuosade m&auml;&auml;ramine teise isiku poolt </eesti>
<inglise>Determination of shares in legacy by another person </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui testaator m&auml;&auml;rab annaku mitmele isikule, v&otilde;ib ta j&auml;tta iga annakusaaja osa suuruse m&auml;&auml;ramise annaku- v&otilde;i testamendit&auml;itja v&otilde;i muu isiku otsustada. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a testator gives a legacy to several persons, he or she may leave determination of the size of the share of the legacy of each legatee to the executor of the legacy, the executor of the will or another person. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud isik ei ole osade suurust m&auml;&auml;ranud ja keeldub seda tegemast, saavad annakusaajad annaku v&otilde;rdsetes osades. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the person specified in subsection (1) of this section does not determine the size of the shares and refuses to do so, the legatees receive the legacy in equal shares. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 59. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 59. </inglise>
<eesti>Aseannakusaaja m&auml;&auml;ramine </eesti>
<inglise>Appointment of alternative legatee </inglise>
<eesti>Testaator v&otilde;ib m&auml;&auml;rata aseannakusaaja. </eesti>
<inglise>A testator may appoint an alternative legatee. </inglise>
<eesti>Aseannakusaaja suhtes kohaldatakse asep&auml;rija kohta k&auml;ivaid s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>Provisions concerning alternative successors apply to alternative legatees. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 60. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 60. </inglise>
<eesti>Annaku m&auml;&auml;ramine p&auml;rijale </eesti>
<inglise>Giving legacy to successor </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Testaator v&otilde;ib lisaks p&auml;randiosale m&auml;&auml;rata p&auml;rijale ka annaku. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In addition to a share of the estate, a testator may also give a legacy to a successor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Annakusaajast p&auml;rijal on iseenda ja annaku teiste saajate vastu samad kohustused kui teistel p&auml;rijatel, kui testamendist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A successor who is a legatee has the same obligations as other successors to themself and to the other recipients of the legacy unless otherwise provided by the will. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) P&auml;rijast annakusaajal on &otilde;igus annakule ka siis, kui ta on p&auml;randist loobunud v&otilde;i pole seda vastu v&otilde;tnud. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A legatee who is a successor has the right to the legacy even if the legatee has renounced or not accepted the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui annak on m&auml;&auml;ratud mitmele p&auml;rijale &uuml;hiselt, on neil sellele &otilde;igus v&otilde;rdeliselt nende p&auml;randiosade suurusega, kui testamendist ei tulene teisti. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a legacy is given to several successors jointly, they have the right thereto in proportion to the size of their shares of the estate unless otherwise provided by the will. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui annakusaajast p&auml;rijale on m&auml;&auml;ratud asep&auml;rija, l&auml;heb &otilde;igus annakule &uuml;le asep&auml;rijale vaid juhul, kui see tuleneb testamendist. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If an alternative successor is appointed to a successor who is a legatee, the right to the legacy transfers to the alternative successor only if so provided by the will. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 61. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 61. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguse tekkimine annakule </eesti>
<inglise>Arising of right to legacy </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Annakusaaja &otilde;igus annakule tekib p&auml;randi avanemisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The right of a legatee to a legacy arises upon the opening of a succession. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui annakusaaja sureb enne p&auml;randi avanemist, ei ole annakusaaja p&auml;rijatel &otilde;igust annakut saada, kui testaator ei ole neid m&auml;&auml;ranud aseannakusaajateks. </eesti>
<inglise>If the legatee dies before the opening of the succession, the successors of the legatee do not have the right to receive the legacy unless the testator has appointed them as alternative legatees. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui annak on m&auml;&auml;ratud edasil&uuml;kkava tingimuse v&otilde;i t&auml;htajaga, tekib annakusaajal &otilde;igus annakule edasil&uuml;kkava tingimuse v&otilde;i t&auml;htp&auml;eva saabumisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a legacy is given with a suspensive condition or a term, the legatee has the right to the legacy upon fulfilment of the suspensive condition or on the due date. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui annakusaaja sureb enne edasil&uuml;kkava tingimuse v&otilde;i t&auml;htp&auml;eva saabumist, ei ole annakusaaja p&auml;rijatel &otilde;igust annakut saada. </eesti>
<inglise>If the legatee dies before fulfilment of the suspensive condition or the due date, the successors of the legatee do not have the right to receive the legacy. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui annak on m&auml;&auml;ratud edasil&uuml;kkava tingimuse v&otilde;i t&auml;htajaga ja annakusaaja sureb p&auml;rast p&auml;randi avanemist ning edasil&uuml;kkava tingimuse v&otilde;i t&auml;htp&auml;eva saabumist, on annakusaaja p&auml;rijatel &otilde;igus annakule. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a legacy is given with a suspensive condition or a term, and the legatee dies after the opening of the succession and fulfilment of the suspensive condition or after the due date, the successors of the legatee have the right to the legacy. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 62. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 62. </inglise>
<eesti>Edasil&uuml;kkava tingimuse v&otilde;i t&auml;htp&auml;evaga m&auml;&auml;ratud annak </eesti>
<inglise>Legacy given with suspensive condition or due date </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui annak on m&auml;&auml;ratud edasil&uuml;kkava tingimuse v&otilde;i t&auml;htajaga ja tingimus v&otilde;i t&auml;htp&auml;ev on saabunud enne p&auml;randi avanemist, loetakse annak m&auml;&auml;ratuks tingimuse v&otilde;i t&auml;htajata. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a legacy is given with a suspensive condition or a term, and the condition is fulfilled or the due date arrives before the opening of the succession, the legacy shall be deemed to be given without a condition or term. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui annak on m&auml;&auml;ratud edasil&uuml;kkava tingimusega, kuid tingimus ei ole saabunud 30 aasta jooksul p&auml;randi avanemisest, kaotab annakusaaja &otilde;iguse annakule. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a legacy is given with a suspensive condition but the condition is not fulfilled within thirty years after the opening of the succession, the legatee loses the right to the legacy. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui annaku t&auml;itmise aeg on j&auml;etud annakut&auml;itja m&auml;&auml;rata, kuid annakut&auml;itja ei ole seda teinud, kuulub annak t&auml;itmisele annakut&auml;itja surma p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If determination of the time for execution of a legacy is left to the executor of the legacy but the executor of the legacy fails to do so, the legacy is subject to execution as of the date of death of the executor of the legacy. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui annakuks on m&auml;&auml;ratud kindel rahasumma v&otilde;i kindel hulk asendatavaid asju, kuid testaator on lubanud annakut&auml;itjal need annakusaajale anda ositi teatud t&auml;htp&auml;evadel ja annakusaaja on surnud p&auml;rast p&auml;randi avanemist, on &otilde;igus saada annak annakusaaja p&auml;rijatel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a definite sum of money or amount of fungibles is given as a legacy, but the testator permits the executor of the legacy to give them to the legatee by instalments on particular dates and the legatee dies after the opening of the succession, the successors of the legatee have the right to receive the legacy. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 63. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 63. </inglise>
<eesti>Annaku vastuv&otilde;tmine ja annakust loobumine </eesti>
<inglise>Acceptance or renunciation of legacy </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Annakusaajal on &otilde;igus annak vastu v&otilde;tta, vastu v&otilde;tmata j&auml;tta v&otilde;i annakust loobuda. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A legatee has the right to accept, not accept or renounce a legacy. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Annaku vastuv&otilde;tmise ja sellest loobumise suhtes kohaldatakse p&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tmise ja p&auml;randist loobumise kohta k&auml;ivaid s&auml;tteid, kui k&auml;esolevast seadusest ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The provisions concerning acceptance or renunciation of succession apply to acceptance or renunciation of a legacy unless otherwise provided by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Edasil&uuml;kkava tingimuse v&otilde;i t&auml;htajaga m&auml;&auml;ratud annakust ei saa loobuda enne tingimuse v&otilde;i t&auml;htp&auml;eva saabumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A legacy given with a suspensive condition or a term cannot be renounced before fulfilment of the suspensive condition or the due date. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui annakusaaja ei v&otilde;ta annakut vastu, loetakse, et annakut ei ole m&auml;&auml;ratud. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a legatee does not accept a legacy, the legacy shall be deemed not to be given. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 64. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 64. </inglise>
<eesti>Annaku osalise vastuv&otilde;tmise keeld </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibition of partial acceptance of legacy </inglise>
<eesti>Annakusaajal ei ole &otilde;igust v&otilde;tta talle m&auml;&auml;ratud annakust vastu vaid osa v&otilde;i annaku osast loobuda. </eesti>
<inglise>A legatee does not have the right to accept only a part of a legacy given to the legatee or to renounce a part of the legacy. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui annakusaajale on m&auml;&auml;ratud mitu annakut, v&otilde;ib ta j&auml;tta m&otilde;ne vastu v&otilde;tmata v&otilde;i m&otilde;nest loobuda. </eesti>
<inglise>If several legacies are given to a legatee, the legatee need not accept or may renounce some of them. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 65. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 65. </inglise>
<eesti>Annaku n&otilde;udmine </eesti>
<inglise>Claiming legacy </inglise>
<eesti>Annakusaaja v&otilde;i aseannakusaaja ei v&otilde;i n&otilde;uda p&auml;rijalt v&otilde;i annakusaajalt annakut enne, kui p&auml;rija v&otilde;i annakusaaja on p&auml;randi vastu v&otilde;tnud. </eesti>
<inglise>A legatee or alternative legatee shall not claim a legacy from a successor or legatee before the successor or legatee accepts the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 66. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 66. </inglise>
<eesti>Annaku hulka kuuluv asi </eesti>
<inglise>Things forming part of legacy </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;randvara hulka kuuluv asi tuleb annakusaajale anda samas seisundis, kui see oli p&auml;randi avanemisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A thing forming part of an estate shall be given to a legatee in the same condition as it was upon the opening of the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>Asi l&auml;heb annakusaajale &uuml;le koos selle juurde kuuluvate &otilde;iguste ja kohustustega, samuti viljaga, mis on saadud annakule &otilde;iguse tekkimise ajast alates annaku hulka kuuluvast asjast v&otilde;i &otilde;igusest. </eesti>
<inglise>A thing transfers to a legatee together with the rights and obligations belonging thereto and the fruit which is received from the thing or a right forming part of the legacy after the right to the legacy arises. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui annak on m&auml;&auml;ratud edasil&uuml;kkava tingimuse v&otilde;i t&auml;htajaga, kuulub annaku hulka kuuluvast asjast kuni tingimuse v&otilde;i t&auml;htp&auml;eva saabumiseni saadud vili annakut&auml;itjale, kui testamendist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a legacy is given with a suspensive condition or a term, the fruit received from a thing forming part of the legacy belongs to the executor of the legacy until fulfilment of the condition or the due date unless otherwise provided by the will. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 67. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 67. </inglise>
<eesti>Annaku hulka kuuluv liigitunnusega asi </eesti>
<inglise>Things with specific characteristics forming part of legacy </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui testaator on kirjeldanud &uuml;ksnes annakuks m&auml;&auml;ratud asja liigitunnuseid ning selliseid asju on p&auml;randis mitu, valib asja annakusaaja, kui testamendist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a testator describes only the specific characteristics of a thing given as a legacy and there are several such things in the estate, the legatee shall select the thing unless otherwise provided by the will. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui testaator on annakut m&auml;&auml;rates kirjeldanud vaid asja liigitunnuseid ja seda asja p&auml;randi hulgas ei ole, peab annaku t&auml;itja andma annakusaajale p&auml;randi arvel muretsetud samasuguste liigitunnustega asja, kui testamendist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If in giving a legacy a testator describes only the specific characteristics of a thing and the estate does not include such thing, the executor of the legacy shall give the legatee a thing with similar specific characteristics procured out of the estate unless otherwise provided by the will. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui testaator on annakuks asja valiku &otilde;iguse andnud kolmandale isikule, kuid see isik ei ole annakule &otilde;iguse tekkimise p&auml;evast kolme kuu jooksul asja valinud, l&auml;heb asja valiku &otilde;igus annakusaajale, kui testamendist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a testator gives to a third person the right to select a thing for a legacy, but the person does not select a thing within three months after the date the right to a legacy arises, the right to select a thing transfers to the legatee unless otherwise provided by the will. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 68. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 68. </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;ue annakuna </eesti>
<inglise>Claim as legacy </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui testaator on annakuks m&auml;&auml;ranud temale kuuluva n&otilde;ude, kuid enne p&auml;randi avanemist on see n&otilde;ue t&auml;idetud ning t&auml;itmisel saadud asi on p&auml;randi hulgas, loetakse see asi m&auml;&auml;ratuks annakusaajale, kui testamendist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a testator gives a claim belonging to him or her as a legacy, but the claim is fulfilled before the opening of the succession and the thing received upon fulfilment is included in the estate, the thing shall be deemed to be given to the legatee unless otherwise provided by the will. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud n&otilde;ue oli rahaline, loetakse raha annakusaajale m&auml;&auml;ratuks ka siis, kui raha p&auml;randi hulgas ei ole. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a claim specified in subsection (1) of this section is monetary, the money shall be deemed to be given to the legatee even if the estate does not include money. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 69. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 69. </inglise>
<eesti>Elatis annakuna </eesti>
<inglise>Support as legacy </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui annakuks on m&auml;&auml;ramata suurusega elatis, lepivad selle suuruses kokku annakusaaja ja annakut&auml;itja ning vaidluse korral otsustab selle kohus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a legacy is support in an unspecified amount, the amount thereof shall be agreed by the legatee and the executor of the legacy or, in the case of a dispute, by a court. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui annakuks on elatis alaealisele isikule, loetakse see m&auml;&auml;ratuks t&auml;isealiseks saamiseni, kui testamendist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a legacy is support for a minor, it shall be deemed to be given until attainment of the age of majority unless otherwise provided by the will. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 70. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 70. </inglise>
<eesti>Annaku koormised </eesti>
<inglise>Duties of legacy </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui annakuks on p&auml;randi hulka kuuluv asi, ei v&otilde;i annakusaaja n&otilde;uda sellel asjal lasuvate koormiste k&otilde;rvaldamist, kui testamendist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a legacy is a thing forming part of an estate, the legatee shall not demand removal of the duties incumbent on the thing unless otherwise provided by the will. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Testaatori &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda asjal lasuvate koormiste k&otilde;rvaldamist kuulub annaku hulka, kui testamendist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The right of a testator to demand removal of the duties incumbent on a thing forms part of the legacy unless otherwise provided by the will. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 71. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 71. </inglise>
<eesti>Annaku t&auml;itmiste koht </eesti>
<inglise>Place for execution of legacy </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui annaku t&auml;itmise kohta ei ole m&auml;&auml;ratud, tuleb asendamatud asjad anda vaidluse korral &uuml;le kohas, kus nad olid p&auml;randi avanemise ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If the place for execution of a legacy is not designated, non-fungible things shall in the case of a dispute be delivered at the place where they were at the time of opening of the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui annakut&auml;itja on asjad m&otilde;juva p&otilde;hjuseta mujale paigutanud, tuleb need &uuml;le anda annakusaaja m&auml;&auml;ratud kohas. </eesti>
<inglise>If the executor of the legacy has placed the things elsewhere without good reason, they shall be delivered at the place designated by the legatee. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui annaku t&auml;itmise kohta ei ole m&auml;&auml;ratud, tuleb asendatavad asjad anda vaidluse korral &uuml;le kohas, kus nende vastuv&otilde;tmine annakusaajale raskusi ei tekita. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the place for execution of a legacy is not designated, fungible things shall in the case of a dispute be delivered at the place where acceptance thereof does not cause inconvenience to the legatee. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui neid asju tuleb v&otilde;tta kinnisasjast, v&otilde;ib need &uuml;le anda kinnisasja asukohas. </eesti>
<inglise>If the things must be taken from an immovable, these may be delivered at the location of the immovable. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 72. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 72. </inglise>
<eesti>Annakut&auml;itja vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Liability of executor of legacy </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui annakuks m&auml;&auml;ratud asi on h&auml;vinud v&otilde;i selle v&auml;&auml;rtus on v&auml;henenud annakut&auml;itja s&uuml;&uuml;l, on annakusaajal &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda temalt kahju h&uuml;vitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a thing given as a legacy is destroyed or its value is decreased due to the fault of the executor of the legacy, the legatee has the right to demand compensation for damage from the executor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui annakuks m&auml;&auml;ratud asi on h&auml;vinud v&otilde;i selle v&auml;&auml;rtus on v&auml;henenud kolmanda isiku s&uuml;&uuml;l, on annakusaajal v&otilde;i annakut&auml;itjal &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda s&uuml;&uuml;dlaselt kahju h&uuml;vitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a thing given as a legacy is destroyed or its value is decreased due to the fault of a third person, the legatee or the executor of the legacy has the right to demand compensation for damage from the offender. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui annakut&auml;itja annaku t&auml;itmisega s&uuml;&uuml;liselt viivitab, peab ta annakusaajale h&uuml;vitama viivitusest tekkinud kahju. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If an executor of a legacy wrongfully delays execution of the legacy, the executor of the legacy shall compensate the legatee for damage caused by the delay. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui viivitusest tekkinud kahjus ei ole s&uuml;&uuml;di annakut&auml;itja, vaid kolmas isik, l&auml;heb annakusaajale koos asjaga &uuml;le &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda s&uuml;&uuml;dlaselt kahju h&uuml;vitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a third person who is not the executor of the legacy is at fault for damage caused by the delay, the right to demand compensation for damage from the offender transfers to the legatee together with the thing. </inglise>
<eesti>6. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 6 </inglise>
<eesti>Sihtk&auml;sund </eesti>
<inglise>Testamentary Obligation </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 73. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 73. </inglise>
<eesti>Sihtk&auml;sundi m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of testamentary obligation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Sihtk&auml;sund on testaatori korraldus, millega ta testamendis paneb p&auml;rijale v&otilde;i annakusaajale (sihtk&auml;sundit&auml;itjad) kohustuse, ilma et kellelgi tekiks sellele kohustusele vastavat &otilde;igust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A testamentary obligation is a disposition by a testator whereby he or she places an obligation on a successor or legatee (executors of a testamentary obligation) in a will without the creation in any person of a right corresponding to the obligation. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui testamendist ei selgu, kas testaator on teinud tingimusega korralduse (&sect; 33) v&otilde;i sihtk&auml;sundi, loetakse, et tehtud on sihtk&auml;sund. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If it is not apparent from a will whether a testator has made a conditional disposition (&sect; 33) or a testamentary obligation, a testamentary obligation shall be deemed to have been made. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 74. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 74. </inglise>
<eesti>Sihtk&auml;sundi t&auml;itmise n&otilde;udmine </eesti>
<inglise>Demand of execution of testamentary obligation </inglise>
<eesti>Sihtk&auml;sundi t&auml;itmist v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda: </eesti>
<inglise>Execution of a testamentary obligation may be demanded by: </inglise>
<eesti>1) p&auml;rija; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a successor; </inglise>
<eesti>2) isik, kes v&otilde;ib astuda sihtk&auml;sundit&auml;itja asemele p&auml;rijana v&otilde;i annakusaajana; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a person who may replace the executor of the testamentary obligation as a successor or legatee; </inglise>
<eesti>3) testamendit&auml;itja; </eesti>
<inglise>3) an executor of the will; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kohalik omavalitsus&uuml;ksus, kui sihtk&auml;sundi t&auml;itmine on &uuml;ldistes huvides. </eesti>
<inglise>4) a local government if execution of the testamentary obligation is in the public interest. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 75. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 75. </inglise>
<eesti>Sihtk&auml;sundi t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmine </eesti>
<inglise>Failure to execute testamentary obligation </inglise>
<eesti>Kui sihtk&auml;sund on sihtk&auml;sundit&auml;itja s&uuml;&uuml;l j&auml;&auml;nud t&auml;itmata, on ta kohustatud p&auml;randi selle osa, mis oleks tulnud &auml;ra kulutada sihtk&auml;sundi t&auml;itmiseks, v&auml;lja andma teistele p&auml;rijatele, nende puudumisel aga isikule, kes astuks sihtk&auml;sundit&auml;itja surma korral tema asemele p&auml;rija v&otilde;i annakusaajana. </eesti>
<inglise>If a testamentary obligation is not executed due to the fault of the executor of the testamentary obligation, the executor of the testamentary obligation is required to deliver the share of the estate which would have been spent for execution of the testamentary obligation to the other successors or, if there are no other successors, to the person who replaces the executor of the testamentary obligation as a successor or legatee upon the death of the executor of the testamentary obligation. </inglise>
<eesti>7. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 7 </inglise>
<eesti>Sihtm&auml;&auml;rang </eesti>
<inglise>Testamentary Direction </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 76. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 76. </inglise>
<eesti>Sihtm&auml;&auml;rangu m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of testamentary direction </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Sihtm&auml;&auml;rang on testaatori korraldus, millega ta m&auml;&auml;rab testamendis p&auml;randile v&otilde;i selle osale sihtotstarbe ja nimetab isiku, kes p&auml;randit v&otilde;i selle osa m&auml;&auml;ratud otstarbel peab valitsema (sihtm&auml;&auml;rangut&auml;itja). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A testamentary direction is a disposition by a testator whereby he or she designates in a will a specific purpose for the estate or a share thereof and nominates a person (executor of a testamentary direction) to administer the estate or a share thereof for the designated purpose. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Sihtm&auml;&auml;rangut&auml;itjaks v&otilde;ib olla olemasolev &otilde;igus- ja teov&otilde;imeline f&uuml;&uuml;siline v&otilde;i juriidiline isik v&otilde;i sihtm&auml;&auml;rangu kohaselt selleks loodav juriidiline isik. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An existing natural or legal person with passive legal capacity and active legal capacity or a legal person established therefor pursuant to the testamentary direction may be the executor of a testamentary direction. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 77. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 77. </inglise>
<eesti>Sihtm&auml;&auml;rangu t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmine </eesti>
<inglise>Failure to execute testamentary direction </inglise>
<eesti>Kui sihtm&auml;&auml;rangut ei t&auml;ideta, v&otilde;ib kohus huvitatud isiku v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse avalduse alusel m&auml;&auml;rata selle t&auml;itmiseks hooldaja, kellel on sel juhul testamendit&auml;itja &otilde;igused ja kohustused. </eesti>
<inglise>If a testamentary direction is not executed, a court may, on the basis of the application of an interested person or a local government, nominate an administrator for execution thereof, who in such case has the rights and obligations of an executor of a will. </inglise>
<eesti>8. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 8 </inglise>
<eesti>Testamendit&auml;itja </eesti>
<inglise>Executor of Will </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 78. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 78. </inglise>
<eesti>Testamendit&auml;itja m&auml;&auml;ramine </eesti>
<inglise>Appointment of executor of will </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Testaator v&otilde;ib testamendis m&auml;&auml;rata selle t&auml;itjaks &uuml;he v&otilde;i mitu isikut. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A testator may appoint in a will one or several persons as an executor of the will. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui m&auml;&auml;ratud isik seda &uuml;lesannet ei t&auml;ida, v&otilde;ib testaator nimetada testamendit&auml;itjaks teise isiku. </eesti>
<inglise>If an appointed person does not perform the duty, the testator may nominate another person as an executor of the will. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Testamendit&auml;itjaks v&otilde;ib m&auml;&auml;rata &uuml;ksnes teov&otilde;imelise isiku. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Only a person with active legal capacity may be appointed as an executor of a will. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 79. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 79. </inglise>
<eesti>Testamendit&auml;itja &uuml;lesande vastuv&otilde;tmine </eesti>
<inglise>Acceptance of duty of executor of will </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Keegi ei ole kohustatud vastu v&otilde;tma testamendit&auml;itja &uuml;lesannet. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) No one is required to accept the duty of executor of a will. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui isik on testamendit&auml;itja &uuml;lesande vastu v&otilde;tnud, ei v&otilde;i ta sellest m&otilde;juva p&otilde;hjuseta loobuda. </eesti>
<inglise>If a person accepts the duty of executor of a will, the person shall not renounce it without good reason. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui testaator on testamendit&auml;itjaks nimetatud isikule m&auml;&auml;ranud annaku ja isik on selle vastu v&otilde;tnud, ei v&otilde;i ta testamendit&auml;itja &uuml;lesande t&auml;itmisest keelduda. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a testator gives a legacy to a person nominated as an executor of the will and the person accepts the legacy, the person shall not refuse performance of the duty of executor of the will. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 80. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 80. </inglise>
<eesti>Testamendit&auml;itja &otilde;igused ja kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Rights and obligations of executor of will </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Testamendit&auml;itja t&auml;idab seadusest ja testamendist tulenevaid &uuml;lesandeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An executor of a will shall perform the duties provided by law and the will. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Testamendit&auml;itja v&otilde;ib testamendis antud &uuml;lesannetest huvitatud isikute n&otilde;usolekul k&otilde;rvale kalduda, kui see on testaatori viimse tahte t&auml;itmise huvides. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An executor of a will may derogate from the duties assigned in the will with the consent of interested persons if this is in the interest of executing the testamentary intention of the testator. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui huvitatud isikud testamendis antud &uuml;lesannetest k&otilde;rvalekaldumisega ei n&otilde;ustu, lahendab vaidluse testamendit&auml;itja n&otilde;udel kohus. </eesti>
<inglise>If the interested persons do not consent to derogation from the duties assigned in the will, a court shall settle the dispute at the request of the executor of the will. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui testamendiga ei ole testamendit&auml;itja &uuml;lesanded m&auml;&auml;ratud, on testamendit&auml;itja kohustatud hoolt kandma, et testaatori viimne tahe saaks t&auml;idetud. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the duties of an executor of a will are not provided by the will, the executor of the will is required to ensure that the testamentary intention of the testator is executed. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui see on testaatori viimse tahte t&auml;itmiseks vajalik, peab testamendit&auml;itja p&auml;randit hoidma ja selle p&auml;rijale ja annakusaajale &uuml;le andma. </eesti>
<inglise>If necessary for execution of the testamentary intention of the testator, the executor of the will shall manage the estate or transfer it to the successor or legatee. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui p&auml;rija ei ole p&auml;randit vastu v&otilde;tnud ning p&auml;randi hooldajat ei ole m&auml;&auml;ratud, t&auml;idab testamendit&auml;itja p&auml;randi valitsemisel hooldaja kohustusi kuni p&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tmiseni v&otilde;i p&auml;randvara hooldaja m&auml;&auml;ramiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a successor does not accept a succession and an administrator of the estate is not nominated, an executor of the will shall perform the obligations of the administrator in the administration of the estate until acceptance of the succession or nomination of an administrator of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) P&auml;randisse kuuluvaid asju v&otilde;ib testamendit&auml;itja v&otilde;&otilde;randada &uuml;ksnes siis, kui see on ette n&auml;htud testamendis v&otilde;i vajalik p&auml;randi korrashoiuks v&otilde;i s&auml;ilitamiseks v&otilde;i testamendi t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An executor of a will may transfer things belonging to the estate only if so provided by the will or if this is necessary for maintenance or preservation of the estate or execution of the will. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Testamendit&auml;itjal on &otilde;igus testamendi t&auml;itmiseks esitada testamendiga &otilde;igustatud isikute huvides n&otilde;udeid kohustatud isikute vastu, kui testamendist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) For execution of a will, an executor of the will has the right to submit claims against obligated persons in the interest of persons entitled by the will unless otherwise provided by the will. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 81. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 81. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randi &uuml;leandmine p&auml;rijale </eesti>
<inglise>Transfer of estate to successor </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui p&auml;rija on p&auml;randi vastu v&otilde;tnud, kuid see ei ole tema valduses, annab testamendit&auml;itja selle p&auml;rijale &uuml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a successor accepts a succession but it is not in the successor's possession, an executor of the will shall transfer it to the successor. </inglise>
<eesti>Testamendit&auml;itja v&otilde;ib enda k&auml;tte j&auml;tta v&otilde;i p&auml;rijalt v&auml;lja n&otilde;uda neid esemeid ja raha, mis on vajalikud annaku v&otilde;i testaatori muu korralduse t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>An executor of the will may retain or reclaim objects and money from a successor which are necessary for execution of a legacy or another disposition by the testator. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui testamendit&auml;itja ei pea testaatori korraldust t&auml;itma isiklikult, v&otilde;ib ta selle t&auml;itmist n&otilde;uda p&auml;rijalt. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If an executor of a will need not themself execute a disposition by the testator, the executor of the will may demand execution thereof by a successor. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 82. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 82. </inglise>
<eesti>Testamendit&auml;itja vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Liability of executor of will </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Testamendit&auml;itja vastutab varaliselt, kui ta on j&auml;tnud seadusest v&otilde;i testamendist tulenevad &uuml;lesanded s&uuml;&uuml;liselt t&auml;itmata. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An executor of a will is proprietarily liable if the executor of the will wrongfully fails to perform the duties provided by law or the will. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui testaator on m&auml;&auml;ranud mitu testamendit&auml;itjat, kuid ei ole &uuml;lesandeid nende vahel jaganud, t&auml;idavad testamendit&auml;itjad oma &uuml;lesandeid &uuml;hiselt ja vastutavad solidaarselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a testator appoints several executors of the will but does not distribute the duties among them, the executors of the will shall perform the duties jointly and are solidarily liable. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;ksikult tegutseda on neil lubatud m&ouml;&ouml;dap&auml;&auml;smatu vajaduse korral. </eesti>
<inglise>They are permitted to act alone in the case of unavoidable necessity. </inglise>
<eesti>Testamendit&auml;itjad vastutavad solidaarselt ka siis, kui nad on &uuml;lesanded omavahel &auml;ra jaganud. </eesti>
<inglise>The executors of the will are solidarily liable even if they distribute the duties among themselves. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui m&otilde;ni testamendit&auml;itja oma &uuml;lesandeid ei t&auml;ida v&otilde;i t&auml;ita ei saa, j&auml;tkavad teised testamendit&auml;itjad testamendi t&auml;itmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If any executor of a will does not or cannot perform the executor's duties, the other executors of the will shall continue execution of the will. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 83. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 83. </inglise>
<eesti>Testamendi t&auml;itmise kulutused ja testamendit&auml;itja tasu </eesti>
<inglise>Expenses for execution of will and remuneration of executor of will </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kulutused, mida testamendit&auml;itja on testamendi t&auml;itmiseks teinud, h&uuml;vitatakse p&auml;randi arvel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Expenses which an executor of a will incurs for execution of the will are reimbursed out of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Testamendit&auml;itja, kes ei ole p&auml;rija ega annakusaaja, v&otilde;ib p&auml;randi arvel oma tegevuse eest tasu saada, kui testamendist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An executor of a will who is not a successor or a legatee may receive remuneration for the executor's activity out of the estate unless otherwise provided by the will. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui p&auml;rijad, annakusaajad ja testamendit&auml;itja ei j&otilde;ua tasu suuruses kokkuleppele, m&auml;&auml;rab testamendit&auml;itja n&otilde;udel tasu suuruse kohus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the successors, legatees and executors of the will fail to agree on the amount of remuneration, a court shall specify the amount of remuneration at the request of an executor of the will. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 84. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 84. </inglise>
<eesti>Testamendit&auml;itja aruanne </eesti>
<inglise>Report of executor of will </inglise>
<eesti>Notar v&auml;ljastab koduse testamendi esitajale testamendi hoiule v&otilde;tmise kohta dokumendi, millele kirjutavad alla testamendi esitaja ja notar. </eesti>
<inglise>An executor of a will shall report on the executor's activity to the successors and legatees at their request unless the testator has released the executor from this duty in the will. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.99 j&otilde;ust.31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 85. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 85. </inglise>
<eesti>Testamendit&auml;itja tagandamine </eesti>
<inglise>Removal of executor of will </inglise>
<eesti>Kui testamendit&auml;itja ei ole oma kohustusi t&auml;itnud, v&otilde;ib kohus ta p&auml;rija, annakusaaja v&otilde;i muu p&auml;randist huvitatud isiku n&otilde;udel tagandada. </eesti>
<inglise>If an executor of a will fails to perform the executor's duties, a court may remove the executor at the request of a successor, legatee or other person who has an interest in the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.99 j&otilde;ust.31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </inglise>
<eesti>9. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 9 </inglise>
<eesti>Testamendi t&uuml;histamine </eesti>
<inglise>Revocation of Will </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 86. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 86. </inglise>
<eesti>Testamendi t&uuml;histamise &otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Right of revocation of will </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Testaator v&otilde;ib testamendi t&uuml;histada hilisema testamendi v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepinguga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A testator may revoke a will by a later will or testamentary contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Notariaalse testamendi v&otilde;ib testaator t&uuml;histada notariaalse v&otilde;i koduse testamendiga v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepinguga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A testator may revoke a notarial will by a notarial or domestic will or a testamentary contract. </inglise>
<eesti>Koduse testamendi v&otilde;ib testaator t&uuml;histada notariaalse v&otilde;i koduse testamendiga v&otilde;i testamendi h&auml;vitamisega v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepinguga. </eesti>
<inglise>A testator may revoke a domestic will by a notarial or domestic will, by destruction of the will or by a testamentary contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui testaator on t&uuml;histanud ainult testamendi m&otilde;ne osa, j&auml;&auml;b testament muus osas kehtima. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a testator revokes only part of a will, the other part of the will remains valid. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Varem tehtud testament kaotab hilisema testamendi v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepinguga kehtivuse niiv&otilde;rd, kuiv&otilde;rd ta on hilisema testamendi v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepinguga vastuolus. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A will made earlier loses validity by a later will or testamentary contract in so far as it is contrary to the later will or testamentary contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui testaator on testamendi t&uuml;histanud, ei j&otilde;ustu t&uuml;histatule eelnenud testamendid, kui t&uuml;histavast testamendist v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepingust ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If a testator revokes his or her will, preceding wills do not enter into force unless otherwise provided by the revoking will or testamentary contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui testaator on notariaalse testamendi koduse testamendiga t&uuml;histanud v&otilde;i seda muutnud ja kodune testament on kaotanud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 25 s&auml;testatud korras kehtivuse, kehtib notariaalne testament. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) If a testator revokes or alters a notarial will by a domestic will and the domestic will becomes invalid pursuant to the procedure provided for in &sect; 25 of this Act, the notarial will is valid. </inglise>
<eesti>10. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 10 </inglise>
<eesti>Abikaasade vastastikune testament </eesti>
<inglise>Reciprocal Will of Spouses </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 87. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 87. </inglise>
<eesti>Abikaasade vastastikuse testamendi m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of reciprocal will of spouses </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Abikaasade vastastikune testament on abikaasade &uuml;hine testament, milles abikaasad nimetavad teineteise vastastikku oma p&auml;rijaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A reciprocal will of spouses is a joint will of the spouses in which the spouses reciprocally nominate one another as their successor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Abikaasade vastastikuses testamendis s&otilde;ltub &uuml;he abikaasa p&auml;rijaks nimetamise kehtivus teise abikaasa p&auml;rijaks nimetamise kehtivusest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In a reciprocal will of spouses, the validity of nomination of one spouse as a successor depends on the validity of nomination of the other spouse as a successor. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Abikaasade vastastikune testament tehakse notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud vormis. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A reciprocal will of spouses shall be made in notarised form. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 88. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 88. </inglise>
<eesti>Abikaasade vastastikune testament kolmanda isiku kasuks </eesti>
<inglise>Reciprocal will of spouses for benefit of third person </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Abikaasad v&otilde;ivad abikaasade vastastikuses testamendis m&auml;&auml;rata, kellele l&auml;heb &uuml;leelanud abikaasa p&auml;rand &uuml;le tema surma korral. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In a reciprocal will of spouses, the spouses may designate to whom the estate of the surviving spouse transfers upon his or her death. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui abikaasade vastastikuses testamendis on m&auml;&auml;ratud, et &uuml;leelanud abikaasa surma korral l&auml;heb tema p&auml;rand &uuml;le kolmandale isikule, ei ole &uuml;leelanud abikaasal, kes on p&auml;randi vastu v&otilde;tnud, &otilde;igust seda abikaasade vastastikuse testamendi korraldust muuta ega oma surma korraks teistsuguseid korraldusi teha. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a reciprocal will of spouses provides that upon the death of the surviving spouse his or her estate transfers to a third person, the surviving spouse who has accepted the succession does not have the right to alter this disposition in the reciprocal will of the spouses or to make different dispositions upon his or her death. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui abikaasade vastastikuses testamendis ei ole m&auml;&auml;ratud, et p&auml;rand peab &uuml;le minema kolmandale isikule varem surnud abikaasa surma p&auml;eval olnud koosseisus, l&auml;heb p&auml;rand kolmandale isikule &uuml;le &uuml;leelanud abikaasa surma p&auml;eval olnud koosseisus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a reciprocal will of spouses does not provide that the estate must transfer to a third person in the form which exists on the date of death of the earlier deceased spouse, the estate shall transfer to the third person in the form which exists on the date of death of the surviving spouse. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui testamendi kohaselt peab p&auml;rand &uuml;le minema kolmandale isikule varem surnud abikaasa surma p&auml;eval olnud koosseisus, on &uuml;leelanud abikaasal p&auml;randi kasutamisel ja k&auml;sutamisel samad &otilde;igused kui eelp&auml;rijal. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If according to the will the estate must transfer to a third person in the form which exists on the date of death of the earlier deceased spouse, the surviving spouse has the same rights as a provisional successor in the use and disposal of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 89. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 89. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;hine annak abikaasade vastastikuses testamendis </eesti>
<inglise>Joint legacy in reciprocal will of spouses </inglise>
<eesti>Kui abikaasad on vastastikuses testamendis m&auml;&auml;ranud &uuml;hise annaku, kuulub see t&auml;itmisele p&auml;rast &uuml;leelanud abikaasa surma, kui testamendist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>If spouses give a joint legacy in a reciprocal will of the spouses, it is subject to execution after the death of the surviving spouse unless otherwise provided by the will. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 90. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 90. </inglise>
<eesti>Eraldi annak abikaasade vastastikuses testamendis </eesti>
<inglise>Separate legacy in reciprocal will of spouses </inglise>
<eesti>Kui abikaasad on vastastikuses testamendis m&auml;&auml;ranud annaku oma lahusvarast, loetakse see iseseisvaks annakuks, mille &uuml;leelanud abikaasa on kohustatud t&auml;itma. </eesti>
<inglise>If spouses give a legacy from their separate property in a reciprocal will of the spouses, it shall be deemed to be an independent legacy which the surviving spouse is required to execute. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 91. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 91. </inglise>
<eesti>Abikaasade vastastikuse testamendi t&uuml;histamine </eesti>
<inglise>Revocation of reciprocal will of spouses </inglise>
<eesti>Abikaasade vastastikuse testamendi v&otilde;ib kumbki abikaasa t&uuml;histada &uuml;hepoolselt. </eesti>
<inglise>Either spouse may revoke a reciprocal will of the spouses unilaterally. </inglise>
<eesti>Testament loetakse t&uuml;histatuks, kui teine abikaasa on k&auml;tte saanud notariaalses korras edastatud teate testamendi t&uuml;histamise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>A will shall be deemed to be revoked when the other spouse receives a notice forwarded by the notarial procedure concerning revocation of a will. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 92. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 92. </inglise>
<eesti>Abikaasade vastastikuse testamendi t&uuml;hisus </eesti>
<inglise>Void reciprocal will of spouses </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui abielu tunnistatakse kehtetuks v&otilde;i lahutatakse, muutub abikaasade vastastikune testament t&uuml;hiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a marriage is declared a nullity or the spouses are divorced, a reciprocal will of the spouses becomes void. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;he abikaasa surma korral v&otilde;ib &uuml;leelanud abikaasa loobuda p&auml;rimisest abikaasade vastastikuse testamendi j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon the death of one spouse, the surviving spouse may renounce the succession pursuant to the reciprocal will of the spouses. </inglise>
<eesti>Sel juhul muutub vastastikune testament t&uuml;hiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case, the reciprocal will becomes void. </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>Testamendi t&uuml;hisus ja vaidlustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Void and Voidable Will </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 93. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 93. </inglise>
<eesti>T&uuml;hine testament </eesti>
<inglise>Void will </inglise>
<eesti>Testament on t&uuml;hine tsiviilseadustiku &uuml;ldosa seaduses (RT I 1994, 53, 889; 89, 1516; 1995, 26-28, 355; 49, 749; 87, 1540) s&auml;testatud alustel, samuti kui testamendi k&otilde;ik korraldused on arusaamatud, m&otilde;ttetud v&otilde;i &uuml;ksteisele vastuk&auml;ivad v&otilde;i kui testament on muutunud t&uuml;hiseks k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 86 ja 92 s&auml;testatud alustel. </eesti>
<inglise>A will is void on the bases provided for in the General Principles of the Civil Code Act (RT I 1994, 53, 889; 89, 1516; 1995, 26-28, 355; 49, 749; 87, 1540) if all testamentary dispositions are incomprehensible, senseless or contradictory, or if the will has become void on the bases provided for in &sect;&sect; 86 and 92 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 94. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 94. </inglise>
<eesti>Vaieldav testament </eesti>
<inglise>Voidable will </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Testamendi v&otilde;i selle osa v&otilde;ib kohus tunnistada kehtetuks tsiviilseadustiku &uuml;ldosa seaduses s&auml;testatud alustel ning &uuml;ksnes p&auml;rast testaatori surma. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A court may declare a will or a part thereof invalid on the bases provided for in the General Principles of the Civil Code Act and only after the death of the testator. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Testamendi v&otilde;i selle osa kehtetuks tunnistamist v&otilde;ivad n&otilde;uda p&auml;rijad, annakusaajad ja teised huvitatud isikud p&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tmiseks s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaja jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Successors, legatees and other interested persons may demand that a will or a part thereof be declared invalid within the term provided for acceptance of the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>4. osa </eesti>
<inglise>Part 4 </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimisleping </eesti>
<inglise>Testamentary Contract </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 95. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 95. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimislepingu m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of testamentary contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;rimislepingu s&otilde;lmib p&auml;randaja teise isiku v&otilde;i isikutega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A bequeather enters into a testamentary contract with another person or other persons. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimislepinguga m&auml;&auml;ratakse p&auml;rijaks v&otilde;i annakusaajaks teine lepingupool v&otilde;i muu isik. </eesti>
<inglise>The other party to the contract or another person is designated as a successor or legatee by the testamentary contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&auml;rimislepingus v&otilde;ib ette n&auml;ha teise lepingupoole kohustused, mis on aluseks p&auml;randi v&otilde;i annaku saamisele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A testamentary contract may prescribe obligations of the other party to the contract which are the basis for receiving the estate or legacy. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) P&auml;rimislepingu, samuti selle muutmise v&otilde;i l&otilde;petamise kokkuleppe s&otilde;lmib p&auml;randaja isiklikult. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A testamentary contract and an agreement to alter or terminate it shall be entered into by the bequeather himself or herself. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) P&auml;rimislepingut ei v&otilde;i &uuml;hepoolselt muuta ega l&otilde;petada, kui seadusest ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A testamentary contract shall not be altered or terminated unilaterally unless otherwise provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 96. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 96. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimislepingu poolte &otilde;igused </eesti>
<inglise>Rights of parties to testamentary contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;rimislepinguga ei v&otilde;i kitsendada p&auml;randaja &otilde;igust vallata, kasutada ja k&auml;sutada oma vara. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The right of a bequeather to possess, use and dispose of his or her property shall not be restricted by a testamentary contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Lepinguj&auml;rgne p&auml;rija v&otilde;i annakusaaja ei omanda p&auml;rimislepingu alusel p&auml;randaja eluajal &otilde;igusi p&auml;randaja varale. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A contractual successor or legatee shall not acquire rights to the property of a bequeather during the lifetime of the bequeather by a testamentary contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui p&auml;randaja on teinud kingituse eesm&auml;rgiga tekitada kahju lepinguj&auml;rgsele p&auml;rijale v&otilde;i annakusaajale, v&otilde;ib lepinguj&auml;rgne p&auml;rija v&otilde;i annakusaaja &uuml;he aasta jooksul p&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tmisest n&otilde;uda kinkelepingu kehtetuks tunnistamist ja kingisaajalt kingi v&auml;ljaandmist alusetu rikastumise s&auml;tete kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a bequeather makes a gift with the purpose of causing damage to a contractual successor or legatee, the contractual successor or legatee may demand that the gratuitous contract be declared invalid and that the gift recipient deliver the gift pursuant to provisions concerning unjust enrichment within one year after acceptance of the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 97. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 97. </inglise>
<eesti>Annak p&auml;rimislepingus </eesti>
<inglise>Legacy in testamentary contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui p&auml;rimislepingus on m&auml;&auml;ratud annak, kuid annakut&auml;itja on m&auml;&auml;ramata, t&auml;idab annaku lepinguj&auml;rgne p&auml;rija samas korras nagu testamendij&auml;rgne p&auml;rija. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a legacy is given in a testamentary contract but an executor of the legacy is not designated, the legacy shall be executed by the contractual successor pursuant to the same procedure as for a testate successor. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui puudub ka lepinguj&auml;rgne p&auml;rija, kohaldatakse testamendij&auml;rgse annaku t&auml;itmise kohta k&auml;ivaid s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>If there is no contractual successor, the provisions concerning execution of testate legacies apply. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Asep&auml;rijal, j&auml;relp&auml;rijal ja annakusaajal on lepinguj&auml;rgse p&auml;rija suhtes samasugused &otilde;igused ja kohustused nagu testamendij&auml;rgse p&auml;rija suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An alternative successor, subsequent successor and legatee have the same rights and obligations with respect to a contractual successor as with respect to a testate successor. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 98. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 98. </inglise>
<eesti>Leping p&auml;rimisest loobumise kohta </eesti>
<inglise>Contract concerning renunciation of succession </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui p&auml;randaja on seadusj&auml;rgse p&auml;rijaga s&otilde;lminud lepingu p&auml;rimisest loobumise kohta, ei ole loobunul &otilde;igust p&auml;randile, sealhulgas ka sundosale, kui lepingust ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a bequeather enters into a contract with an intestate successor concerning renunciation of a succession, the renouncer does not have the right to the estate, including the compulsory portion, unless otherwise provided by the contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&auml;rimislepingus, millega seadusj&auml;rgne p&auml;rija loobub p&auml;rimisest, v&otilde;idakse ette n&auml;ha, et loobunu asemel p&auml;rib teine isik. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A testamentary contract whereby an intestate successor renounces a succession may prescribe that another person succeeds in place of the renouncer. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui seadusj&auml;rgne p&auml;rija on p&auml;rimisest loobunud kaasp&auml;rijate kasuks neid t&auml;psemalt nimetamata, loetakse, et loobutud on nende p&auml;rijate kasuks, kes p&otilde;lvnevad loobunuga &uuml;hisest l&auml;hemast &uuml;lenejast sugulasest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If an intestate successor renounces a succession for the benefit of co-successors without designating them specifically, the renunciation shall be deemed to be for the benefit of the successors who descend from the nearest common ascendant of the renouncer. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui p&auml;randaja ei ole testamendis ega p&auml;rimislepingus teinud korraldusi vara suhtes, mille p&auml;rimisest seadusj&auml;rgne p&auml;rija on loobunud, on nimetatud p&auml;randile &otilde;igus p&auml;randaja teistel seadusj&auml;rgsetel p&auml;rijatel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a bequeather does not make in a will or testamentary contract a disposition of property the succession of which an intestate successor has renounced, the other intestate successors of the bequeather have the right to the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 99. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 99. </inglise>
<eesti>Lepinguga p&auml;rimisest loobunu alanejate sugulaste p&auml;rimis&otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Right of succession of descendants of renouncer of succession by contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui p&auml;rimislepingu j&auml;rgi p&auml;rimisest loobunu on p&auml;randaja surma ajal elus, ei p&auml;ri tema alanejad sugulased, kui lepinguga ei ole ette n&auml;htud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a renouncer of a succession by a testamentary contract is alive at the time of death of the bequeather, the descendants of the renouncer do not succeed unless otherwise prescribed by the contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui p&auml;randaja alaneja v&otilde;i k&uuml;lgjoones sugulane on p&auml;rimisest loobunud p&auml;rimislepingu alusel ja surnud enne p&auml;randajat, p&auml;rivad loobunu alanejad sugulased, kui lepinguga pole ette n&auml;htud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a descendant or collateral relative of a bequeather renounces the succession by a testamentary contract and dies before the bequeather, the descendants of the renouncer succeed unless otherwise prescribed by the contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Vara, mille p&auml;rimislepingu alusel p&auml;rimisest loobunu on p&auml;randaja elu ajal saanud loobumise tasuks, arvatakse p&auml;randi hulka, kui loobunu alanejad sugulased on p&auml;randi vastu v&otilde;tnud. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Property which a renouncer of a succession by a testamentary contract receives during the lifetime of the bequeather as compensation for renunciation shall be deemed to be part of the estate if the descendants of the renouncer accept the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 100. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 100. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimislepingu vorm </eesti>
<inglise>Form of testamentary contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;rimisleping s&otilde;lmitakse notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud vormis. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A testamentary contract shall be entered into in notarised form. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Lepingupooled v&otilde;ivad lepingut muuta v&otilde;i selle l&otilde;petada notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud kokkuleppega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Parties to a testamentary contract may alter or terminate the contract by a notarised agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 101. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 101. </inglise>
<eesti>Kolmas isik p&auml;rimislepingus </eesti>
<inglise>Third person in testamentary contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui kolmas isik, kes on p&auml;rimislepinguga m&auml;&auml;ratud p&auml;rijaks v&otilde;i annaku saajaks, p&auml;randist loobub v&otilde;i p&auml;randit v&otilde;i annakut vastu ei v&otilde;ta, kaotab leping selles osas kehtivuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a third person who is designated as a successor or legatee by a testamentary contract renounces the succession or does not accept the succession or legacy, that part of the contract becomes invalid. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&auml;rimislepingu pooled v&otilde;ivad lepingut muuta v&otilde;i selle l&otilde;petada kolmanda isiku n&otilde;usolekuta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The parties to the testamentary contract may alter or terminate the contract without the consent of the third person. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 102. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 102. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimislepingu &uuml;hepoolne muutmine v&otilde;i l&otilde;petamine </eesti>
<inglise>Unilateral alteration or termination of testamentary contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;randaja v&otilde;ib p&auml;rimislepingut &uuml;hepoolselt notariaalse testamendiga muuta v&otilde;i selle l&otilde;petada, kui isik, kelle kasuks p&auml;rimisleping on tehtud, on toime pannud kuriteo p&auml;randaja v&otilde;i tema abikaasa v&otilde;i p&auml;randaja alaneja v&otilde;i &uuml;leneja sugulase vastu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A bequeather may alter or terminate a testamentary contract unilaterally by a notarial will if a person for whose benefit the testamentary contract is made commits an offence against the bequeather, the bequeather's spouse, descendant or ascendant. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&auml;rimisleping loetakse muudetuks v&otilde;i l&otilde;petatuks, kui teine lepingupool on k&auml;tte saanud notariaalses korras edastatud teate p&auml;rimislepingu muutmise v&otilde;i l&otilde;petamise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A testamentary contract shall be deemed to be altered or terminated if the other party to the contract receives a notice sent by the notarial procedure concerning alteration or termination of the testamentary contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 103. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 103. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimislepingu kehtetus </eesti>
<inglise>Invalidity of testamentary contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;rimisleping on t&uuml;hine tsiviilseadustiku &uuml;ldosa seaduses s&auml;testatud alustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A testamentary contract is void on the bases provided for in the General Principles of the Civil Code Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kohus v&otilde;ib tunnistada p&auml;rimislepingu kehtetuks tsiviilseadustiku &uuml;ldosa seaduses s&auml;testatud alustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A court may declare a testamentary contract invalid on the bases provided for in the General Principles of the Civil Code Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) P&auml;rimislepingu kehtetuks tunnistamist v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda p&auml;randaja, p&auml;rast tema surma aga p&auml;rijad, annakusaajad ja teised huvitatud isikud p&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tmiseks s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaja jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The declaration of invalidity of a testamentary contract may be demanded by a bequeather, or after his or her death, by the successors, legatees and other interested persons within the term provided for acceptance of the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui p&auml;rimislepinguga on ette n&auml;htud, et isik, kelle kasuks on p&auml;rimislepingus tehtud korraldus, peab p&auml;rimislepingu kohaselt andma p&auml;randajale &uuml;lalpidamist v&otilde;i tegema p&auml;randaja kasuks teatud teo, kuid neid kohustusi ei t&auml;ida, v&otilde;ib p&auml;randaja n&otilde;uda kohustuste t&auml;itmist v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepingu v&otilde;i selle osa kehtetuks tunnistamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a testamentary contract prescribes that the person for whose benefit a disposition is made in the testamentary contract must, according to the testamentary contract, provide maintenance to the bequeather or perform a particular act for the benefit of the bequeather but the person fails to perform these duties, the bequeather may demand performance of the duties or the declaration of invalidity of the testamentary contract or a part thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui seadusj&auml;rgne p&auml;rija on p&auml;rimislepingu alusel p&auml;rimisest loobunud p&otilde;hjusel, et ta pidi loobumise eest tasu saama, kuid seda ei saanud, on tal &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda p&auml;rimislepingu v&otilde;i selle osa kehtetuks tunnistamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If an intestate successor renounces a succession by a testamentary contract on the ground that the intestate successor was to receive compensation for renunciation but did not receive it, the intestate successor has the right to demand that the testamentary contract or a part thereof be declared invalid. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui &uuml;he lepingupoole p&auml;rimislepingus etten&auml;htud kohustus tunnistatakse kehtetuks, on kehtetu ka teise poole vastav kohustus. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) If an obligation of one party to a testamentary contract prescribed in the contract is declared invalid, the corresponding obligation of the other party is also invalid. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Kui p&auml;rimislepinguj&auml;rgne p&auml;rija v&otilde;i annakusaaja sureb enne p&auml;randajat, j&otilde;udmata lepingust tulenevat kohustust olulisel m&auml;&auml;ral t&auml;ita, loetakse p&auml;rimisleping kehtetuks algusest peale. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) If a successor or legatee by a testamentary contract dies before the bequeather without being able to perform an obligation arising from the contract to a significant extent, the testamentary contract shall be deemed to be invalid from inception. </inglise>
<eesti>5. osa </eesti>
<inglise>Part 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Sundosa </eesti>
<inglise>Compulsory Portion </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 104. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 104. </inglise>
<eesti>Sundosa p&auml;rimine </eesti>
<inglise>Succession of compulsory portion </inglise>
<eesti>Kui p&auml;randaja on testamendi v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepinguga j&auml;tnud p&auml;randist ilma seaduse j&auml;rgi p&auml;rima &otilde;igustatud t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetu &uuml;leneja v&otilde;i alaneja sugulase v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetu abikaasa v&otilde;i on seadusj&auml;rgse p&auml;rimisega v&otilde;rreldes nende p&auml;randiosi v&auml;hendanud, on nendel sugulastel ja abikaasal &otilde;igus p&auml;rida sundosa. </eesti>
<inglise>If a bequeather has by a will or testamentary contract disinherited an ascendant, descendant or his or her spouse who are incapacitated for work and are entitled to succeed in intestacy, or has reduced their shares of the estate as compared to their shares according to intestate succession, the relatives and spouse have the right to succeed to the compulsory portion. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 105. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 105. </inglise>
<eesti>Sundosa suurus </eesti>
<inglise>Size of compulsory portion </inglise>
<eesti>Sundosa on pool p&auml;randiosast, mille p&auml;rija oleks seadusj&auml;rgse p&auml;rimise korral saanud, kui p&auml;randi oleksid vastu v&otilde;tnud k&otilde;ik seadusj&auml;rgsed p&auml;rijad. </eesti>
<inglise>A compulsory portion is one-half of the share of an estate which a successor would have received in the case of intestate succession if all intestate successors would have accepted the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 106. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 106. </inglise>
<eesti>Sundossa kuuluv vara </eesti>
<inglise>Property belonging to compulsory portion </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Sundossa kuuluva vara kindlakstegemisel v&otilde;etakse aluseks p&auml;randi hulka kuuluv vara p&auml;randi avanemise p&auml;eva seisuga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Determination of property belonging to the compulsory portion shall be based on the property which forms part of the estate as at the date of opening of the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Sundosa m&auml;&auml;ramisel arvestatakse p&auml;randina ka eelp&auml;randit (&sect; 156) ja p&auml;randaja poolt teistele isikutele sundosa v&auml;hendamise eesm&auml;rgil viimase kolme aasta jooksul enne p&auml;randaja surma tehtud kingitusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the specification of the compulsory portion, provisional successions (&sect; 156) and gifts made by the bequeather to other persons within the last three years before the death of the bequeather for the purpose of reducing the compulsory portion shall also be considered part of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Sundosa m&auml;&auml;ramisel ei arvestata p&auml;randina p&auml;randaja v&otilde;lga, matmiskulusid, p&auml;randvara nimekirja koostamise ja p&auml;randvara hindamise kulusid ning p&auml;randaja &uuml;lalpidamisel olnud isikute &uuml;he kuu &uuml;lalpidamise kulusid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In the specification of the compulsory portion, the debts and burial expenses of the bequeather, expenditure for preparation of an inventory of the estate and valuation of the estate, and one month's maintenance expenditure for persons who were maintained by the bequeather shall not be considered part of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Sundosana saab p&auml;rija eelk&otilde;ige vara, mille p&auml;randaja on sundosa saajale oma viimse tahte kohaselt m&auml;&auml;ranud. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) As the compulsory portion, a successor shall first receive the property which the bequeather gives to the recipient of a compulsory portion according to the testamentary intention of the bequeather. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui seda vara on sundosa suurusest v&auml;hem, arvatakse puuduv osa sundosasse muust p&auml;randvarast. </eesti>
<inglise>If the property is less than the size of the compulsory portion, the missing share shall be included in the compulsory portion from another part of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui p&auml;randvara on sundosa suurusest v&auml;hem, on sundosa saajal &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud kingitusi kingisaajatelt alates k&otilde;ige hilisemast kinkest enne p&auml;randaja surma. </eesti>
<inglise>If the estate is less than the size of the compulsory portion, the recipient of the compulsory portion has the right to demand the gifts specified in subsection (2) of this section from the gift recipients, commencing with the latest gift before the death of the bequeather. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui kinked on tehtud &uuml;heaegselt, vastutavad kingisaajad sundosa saaja ees v&otilde;rdeliselt kingituse suurusega. </eesti>
<inglise>If gifts are made concurrently, the gift recipients are liable to the recipient of the compulsory portion in proportion to the size of the gift. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kingisaaja vastu k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 4 nimetatud n&otilde;ude esitamise aegumist&auml;htaeg on &uuml;ks aasta, arvates p&auml;evast, mil sundosa saaja on p&auml;randi vastu v&otilde;tnud. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The limitation period for submission of the claim specified in subsection (4) of this section against a gift recipient is one year after the date the recipient of the compulsory portion accepts the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 107. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 107. </inglise>
<eesti>Sundosa koormamise keeld </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibition of encumbrance of compulsory portion </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randiosa suhtes, mille p&auml;rija on saanud sundosana, ei kehti p&auml;randaja korraldused tingimuse, t&auml;htaja, annaku v&otilde;i muu kohustuse suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise>Dispositions by a bequeather which include a condition or term, legacy or another obligation are not valid with respect to a share of the estate which a successor receives as a compulsory portion. </inglise>
<eesti>Sundosa p&auml;rijale ei saa m&auml;&auml;rata j&auml;relp&auml;rijat. </eesti>
<inglise>A subsequent successor cannot be designated to the successor of a compulsory portion. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 108. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 108. </inglise>
<eesti>Sundosast ilmaj&auml;tmine </eesti>
<inglise>Disinheritance of compulsory portion </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;randaja v&otilde;ib testamendi v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepinguga sundosast ilma j&auml;tta isiku, kes on p&auml;randaja, tema abikaasa v&otilde;i p&auml;randaja alaneja v&otilde;i &uuml;leneja sugulase vastu toime pannud kuriteo. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A bequeather may by a will or testamentary contract disinherit of a compulsory portion a person who commits a criminal offence against the bequeather, the bequeather's spouse, ascendant or descendant. </inglise>
<eesti>Sel juhul peab p&auml;randaja v&auml;ljendama sundosast ilmaj&auml;tmise p&otilde;hjuse. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case, the bequeather shall express the reason for disinheritance of the compulsory portion. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Sundosa p&auml;rija n&otilde;udel v&otilde;ib kohus sundosast ilmaj&auml;tmise tunnistada kehtetuks, kui p&auml;randaja on ilmaj&auml;tmise p&otilde;hjuse j&auml;tnud m&auml;rkimata v&otilde;i p&otilde;hjus ei vasta k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatule. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) At the request of a successor of a compulsory portion, a court may declare disinheritance of the compulsory portion invalid if the bequeather fails to indicate the reason for the disinheritance or the reason is not in accordance with the provisions of subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 109. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 109. </inglise>
<eesti>Sundosa &uuml;leminek sundosast ilmaj&auml;tmise korral </eesti>
<inglise>Transfer of compulsory portion in case of disinheritance of compulsory portion </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui p&auml;randaja ei ole m&auml;&auml;ranud teisiti, l&auml;heb sundosast ilmaj&auml;etud p&auml;rija sundosa p&auml;randaja seadusj&auml;rgsetele p&auml;rijatele samadel alustel nagu ei oleks sundosast ilmaj&auml;etu p&auml;randi avanemise ajal elus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Unless otherwise specified by a bequeather, the compulsory portion of a successor who is disinherited of the compulsory portion transfers to the intestate successors of the bequeather on the same bases as if the person disinherited of the compulsory portion were not alive at the time of opening of the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Sundosast ilmaj&auml;etud p&auml;rija alanejatel sugulastel tekib &otilde;igus p&auml;rida sundosa samadel alustel nagu ei oleks sundosast ilmaj&auml;etu p&auml;randi avanemise ajal elus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The right to succeed to the compulsory portion arises in the descendants of a successor who is disinherited of the compulsory portion on the same bases as if the person disinherited of the compulsory portion were not alive at the time of opening of the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>6. osa </eesti>
<inglise>Part 6 </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimise k&auml;ik </eesti>
<inglise>Succession Process </inglise>
<eesti>1. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 1 </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randi hoid </eesti>
<inglise>Management of Estate </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 110. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 110. </inglise>
<eesti>Hoiumeetmed </eesti>
<inglise>Management measures </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;randaja surma korral v&otilde;ib kohus rakendada p&auml;randvara hoiumeetmeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon the death of a bequeather a court may apply measures for management of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&auml;randvara hoiumeetmed on: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The measures for management of an estate are: </inglise>
<eesti>1) p&auml;randvara valitsemise korraldamine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) organisation of administration of the estate; </inglise>
<eesti>2) p&auml;randaja vara eraldamine p&auml;rija varast (&sect; 114); </eesti>
<inglise>2) separation of the property of the bequeather from the property of a successor (&sect; 114); </inglise>
<eesti>3) p&auml;randi avanemise teate avaldamine &uuml;leriigilises p&auml;evalehes; </eesti>
<inglise>3) publication of a notice concerning the opening of the succession in a national daily newspaper; </inglise>
<eesti>4) tsiviilkohtupidamise seadustikus (RT I 1993, 31/32, 538; 1994, 1, 5; 1995, 29, 358; 1996, 3, 57) s&auml;testatud hagi tagamise abin&otilde;ude rakendamine. </eesti>
<inglise>4) application of measures to secure an action provided for in the Code of Civil Procedure (RT I 1993, 31/32, 538; 1994, 1, 5; 1995, 29, 358; 1996, 3, 57). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 111. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 111. </inglise>
<eesti>Hoiumeetmete rakendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Application of management measures </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kohus rakendab p&auml;randvara hoiumeetmeid notari, p&auml;rija, p&auml;randi hooldaja, testamendit&auml;itja, p&auml;randaja v&otilde;lausaldaja, p&auml;randisse kuuluva vara kaas- v&otilde;i &uuml;hisomaniku v&otilde;i teiste huvitatud isikute taotlusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A court shall apply measures for management of an estate at the request of a notary, successor, administrator of the estate, executor of the will, creditor of the bequeather, co-owner or joint owner of the property belonging to the estate, or other interested persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kohus rakendab huvitatud isikute &otilde;iguste kaitseks oma algatusel p&auml;randvara hoiumeetmeid, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A court shall apply measures for management of an estate on its own initiative for protection of the rights of interested persons if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) p&auml;rija ei ole teada; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a successor is not known; </inglise>
<eesti>2) p&auml;rija ei viibi p&auml;randvara asukohas; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a successor is not in the location of the estate; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ei ole teada, kas p&auml;rija v&otilde;i tema esindaja on p&auml;randi vastu v&otilde;tnud v&otilde;i sellest loobunud; </eesti>
<inglise>3) it is not known if a successor or the successor's representative has accepted or renounced the succession; </inglise>
<eesti>4) p&auml;rija on teov&otilde;imetu; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a successor is without active legal capacity; </inglise>
<eesti>5) p&auml;randil lasuvad v&otilde;lad v&otilde;ivad &uuml;letada p&auml;randi suuruse. </eesti>
<inglise>5) the debts incumbent on the estate may exceed the size of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kohus v&otilde;ib keelduda hoiumeetmetest, kui kulutused ilmselt ei vasta p&auml;randvara suurusele, samuti kui meetmeid ei ole vaja huvitatud isiku &otilde;iguste tagamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A court may refuse to apply management measures if the expenses are evidently not in accordance with the size of the estate and if measures are not necessary to guarantee the rights of interested persons. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 112. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 112. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randvara valitsemine </eesti>
<inglise>Administration of estate </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;randvara valitsemiseks nimetab kohus p&auml;randi hooldaja, kellele kohus v&otilde;ib anda korraldusi vara valdamiseks, kasutamiseks ning k&auml;sutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A court shall nominate an administrator for administration of an estate, to whom the court may issue orders for possession, use and disposal of property. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kohus nimetab hooldajaks p&auml;randist huvitatud isiku, huvitatud isiku poolt soovitatud isiku v&otilde;i muu isiku. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A court shall nominate a person who has an interest in the estate, a person recommended by an interested person or another person as the administrator. </inglise>
<eesti>Hooldajaks v&otilde;ib olla isik, kes saab p&auml;randit n&otilde;uetekohaselt valitseda. </eesti>
<inglise>A person who is able to administer the estate as required may be the administrator. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohus v&otilde;ib isiku, kes p&auml;randit n&otilde;uetekohaselt ei valitse, hooldajakohustustest vabastada. </eesti>
<inglise>The court may release a person who fails to administer an estate as required from the administration obligations. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Hooldaja on kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An administrator is required to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kohtu m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htaja jooksul esitama kohtule p&auml;randvara nimekirja; </eesti>
<inglise>1) submit an inventory of the estate to a court within the term specified by the court; </inglise>
<eesti>2) vara heaperemehelikult valitsema ning tagama selle s&auml;ilimise; </eesti>
<inglise>2) administer property prudently and ensure its preservation; </inglise>
<eesti>3) andma p&auml;randvara arvel &uuml;lalpidamist isikule, keda p&auml;randaja oli seaduse alusel kohustatud &uuml;lal pidama; </eesti>
<inglise>3) provide maintenance out of the estate to a person whom the bequeather was required to maintain pursuant to law; </inglise>
<eesti>4) tasuma p&auml;randvara arvel p&auml;randaja v&otilde;lad; </eesti>
<inglise>4) pay the debts of the bequeather out of the estate; </inglise>
<eesti>5) aru andma vara valitsemisest kohtule ja p&auml;rijatele. </eesti>
<inglise>5) report on administration of the property to the court and successors. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Hooldajal ei ole &otilde;igust kohtu loata v&otilde;&otilde;randada p&auml;randisse kuuluvat kinnisasja. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An administrator does not have the right to transfer immovables belonging to an estate without court authorisation. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) P&auml;rijal ei ole &otilde;igust k&auml;sutada p&auml;randvara, mis on antud hooldaja valitseda. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A successor does not have the right to dispose of the estate which is transferred to an administrator to administer. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kohus l&otilde;petab p&auml;randvara valitsemise, kui on &auml;ra langenud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 111 s&auml;testatud hoiumeetmete rakendamise alused. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A court shall terminate administration of an estate if the bases for application of management measures provided for in &sect; 111 of this Act cease to exist. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 113. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 113. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randvara hooldamise tasu </eesti>
<inglise>Remuneration for maintenance of estate </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randvara hooldajal on &otilde;igus saada p&auml;randvara valitsemise eest p&auml;randi arvel tasu. </eesti>
<inglise>The administrator of an estate has the right to receive remuneration out of the estate for administration of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>Hooldamise tasu suuruse m&auml;&auml;rab kohus. </eesti>
<inglise>The amount of remuneration for administration shall be specified by a court. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 114. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 114. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randvara eraldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Separation of estate </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui p&auml;rija tegevus v&otilde;i tema varaline seisund v&otilde;ib kahjustada annakusaaja v&otilde;i isiku huve, kellel on n&otilde;ue p&auml;randi suhtes, v&otilde;ib kohus huvitatud isiku n&otilde;udel eraldada p&auml;randaja vara p&auml;rija varast ning nimetada p&auml;randvara valitsemiseks hooldaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If the activity of a successor or the successor's proprietary situation may damage the interests of a legatee or of a person who has a claim with respect to the estate, a court may separate the property of the bequeather from the property of the successor at the request of an interested person and nominate an administrator to administer the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eraldatud p&auml;randvara arvel t&auml;idetakse p&auml;randvaral lasuvad kohustused k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 134 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The obligations incumbent on an estate are performed out of the separated estate pursuant to the procedure provided for in &sect; 134 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;uete rahuldamisest &uuml;le j&auml;&auml;nud p&auml;randvara antakse p&auml;rijatele. </eesti>
<inglise>The residual estate remaining after satisfaction of claims is transferred to the successors. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) P&auml;randvara eraldamist n&otilde;udnud isik ei saa taotleda oma n&otilde;ude rahuldamist p&auml;rija vara arvel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A person who requests separation of an estate cannot request satisfaction of the person's claim out of the property of a successor. </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tmine ja p&auml;randist loobumine </eesti>
<inglise>Acceptance and Renunciation of Succession </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 115. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 115. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastuv&otilde;tmise ja loobumise p&ouml;&ouml;rdumatus </eesti>
<inglise>Irrevocability of acceptance and renunciation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;rija v&otilde;ib p&auml;randi vastu v&otilde;tta v&otilde;i p&auml;randist loobuda. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A successor may accept or renounce a succession. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&auml;rast p&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tmist ei saa sellest enam loobuda. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A succession can no longer be renounced after acceptance. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rast p&auml;randist loobumist ei saa seda enam vastu v&otilde;tta. </eesti>
<inglise>A succession can no longer be accepted after renunciation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 116. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 116. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastuv&otilde;tmine ja loobumine testamendi ja lepingu j&auml;rgi </eesti>
<inglise>Acceptance and renunciation by will or contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui testamendi- v&otilde;i lepinguj&auml;rgne p&auml;rija on p&auml;randist loobunud, ei saa ta testamendi v&otilde;i lepinguga temale m&auml;&auml;ratud p&auml;randit seadusj&auml;rgselt p&auml;rida, v&auml;lja arvatud p&auml;randi sundosa. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a testate or contractual successor renounces a succession, the testate or contractual successor cannot by a will or contract succeed in intestacy to the estate given to the testate or contractual successor except the compulsory portion of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui p&auml;rija on &otilde;igustatud p&auml;rima nii testamendi kui ka lepingu j&auml;rgi, v&otilde;ib ta p&auml;randi vastu v&otilde;tta omal valikul kas testamendi v&otilde;i lepingu j&auml;rgi v&otilde;i m&otilde;lema j&auml;rgi, kui testament ja leping ei ole omavahel vastuolus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a successor is entitled to succeed both by testate and contractual succession, the successor may at the successor's discretion accept the succession either by will or contract or by both unless the will and the contract are contradictory. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 117. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 117. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastuv&otilde;tmise ja loobumise kord </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for acceptance or renunciation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tmiseks v&otilde;i sellest loobumiseks tuleb k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 118 s&auml;testatud t&auml;htajal esitada p&auml;randi avanemise koha notarile avaldus, mille notar t&otilde;estab. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For acceptance or renunciation of a succession, a written application shall be submitted to a notary of the place of opening of the succession by the deadline provided for in &sect; 118 of this Act and the notary shall attest the application. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui p&auml;rand avanes v&auml;lismaal ja p&auml;rimisele kohaldatakse Eesti seadust, esitatakse avaldus notarile, kelle t&ouml;&ouml;piirkonnas p&auml;randvara asub. </eesti>
<inglise>If a succession opens in a foreign state and Estonian law applies to the succession, the application shall be submitted to the notary in whose territorial jurisdiction the estate is located. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.99 j&otilde;ust.31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&auml;rija, kes p&auml;randvara valdab, kasutab v&otilde;i k&auml;sutab, v&otilde;ib p&auml;randist loobuda, esitades p&auml;randist loobumise avalduse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 118 s&auml;testatud t&auml;htajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A successor who possesses, uses or disposes of the estate may renounce the succession by submitting an application for renunciation of the succession by the deadline provided for in &sect; 118 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui p&auml;rija ei ole esitanud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud avaldust ega avaldust p&auml;randist loobumise kohta, kuid on asunud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 118 s&auml;testatud t&auml;htajal p&auml;randvara v&otilde;i selle osa valdama, kasutama v&otilde;i k&auml;sutama, loetakse ta p&auml;randi vastu v&otilde;tnuks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a successor does not submit the application specified in subsection (1) of this section or an application concerning renunciation of the succession but has commenced possession, use or disposal of the estate or a share thereof by the deadline provided for in &sect; 118 of this Act, the successor shall be deemed to have accepted the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui p&auml;rima &otilde;igustatud isik ei ole k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 118 s&auml;testatud t&auml;htajal p&auml;randvara valdama, kasutama v&otilde;i k&auml;sutama asunud ega p&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tmise v&otilde;i p&auml;randist loobumise avaldust esitanud, on ta &otilde;iguse p&auml;randile kaotanud ning tema p&auml;randiosa jagatakse p&auml;randi vastu v&otilde;tnud p&auml;rijate vahel juurdekasvu&otilde;iguse alusel (&sect; 127-129). </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a person entitled to succeed has not commenced possession, use or disposal of the estate by the deadline provided for in &sect; 118 of this Act or submitted an application for acceptance or renunciation of the succession, the person loses the right to the estate and the person's share of the estate is divided on the basis of the right of accretion (&sect; 127-129) among the successors who accept the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 118. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 118. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastuv&otilde;tmise v&otilde;i loobumise t&auml;htaeg </eesti>
<inglise>Term for acceptance or renunciation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Notar v&otilde;ib p&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tmiseks v&otilde;i sellest loobumiseks anda t&auml;htaja, saates selle kohta kirjaliku teate p&auml;rima &otilde;igustatud isikule v&otilde;i avaldades teadaande ametlikus v&auml;ljaandes Ametlikud Teadaanded. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A notary may provide a term for acceptance or renunciation of a succession and send a written notice thereof to a person entitled to succeed, or publish a notice in the official publication Ametlikud Teadaanded. </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;htaeg ei v&otilde;i olla l&uuml;hem kui kaks kuud teate k&auml;ttesaamisest v&otilde;i avaldamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>The term shall not be shorter than two months after receipt or publication of the notice. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.01.99 j&otilde;ust.01.03.99 - RT I 1999, 10, 155; 10.11.99 j&otilde;ust.31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.01.99 entered into force 01.03.99 - RT I 1999, 10, 155; 10.11.99 entered into force 31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&auml;rima &otilde;igustatud isiku avalduse alusel v&otilde;ib notar k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud t&auml;htaega m&otilde;juvatel p&otilde;hjustel m&otilde;istliku aja v&otilde;rra pikendada. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) On the basis of an application of a person entitled to succeed, a notary may extend the term specified in subsection (1) of this section for good reason by a reasonable period of time. </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;htaja pikendamisest teatab notar k&otilde;igile p&auml;rima &otilde;igustatud isikutele. </eesti>
<inglise>The notary shall notify all persons who are entitled to succeed of an extension of the term. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.99 j&otilde;ust.31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </inglise>
<eesti>(2 (1)) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud t&auml;htaja v&otilde;ib p&auml;rima &otilde;igustatud isiku avalduse alusel ennistada: </eesti>
<inglise>(2 (1)) The term specified in subsection (1) of this section may be restored on the basis of an application of a person entitled to succeed: </inglise>
<eesti>1) vaidluse korral kohus, kui ta loeb t&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dalastuks m&otilde;juval p&otilde;hjusel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) by a court in the case of a dispute if the court considers that the term was allowed to expire for good reason; </inglise>
<eesti>2) vaidluse puudumise korral notar, kui k&otilde;ik p&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tnud isikud esitavad kirjaliku notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud allkirjaga n&otilde;usoleku. </eesti>
<inglise>2) by a notary in the absence of a dispute if all persons who have accepted the succession submit written consent with a notarised signature. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.99 j&otilde;ust.31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) P&auml;randit ei saa vastu v&otilde;tta ega sellest loobuda, kui p&auml;randi avanemisest on m&ouml;&ouml;dunud 10 aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A succession cannot be accepted or renounced if ten years have passed after the opening of the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui p&auml;randaja on surnuks tunnistatud, ei saa p&auml;randit vastu v&otilde;tta ega sellest loobuda, kui surnuks tunnistamise kohtuotsuse j&otilde;ustumisest on m&ouml;&ouml;dunud 10 aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a bequeather is declared dead, the succession cannot be accepted or renounced if ten years have passed after the entry into force of the declaration of death order. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 119. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 119. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastuv&otilde;tmise ja loobumise &otilde;iguse p&auml;ritavus </eesti>
<inglise>Succession of right to accept and renounce </inglise>
<eesti>Kui p&auml;rima &otilde;igustatud isik sureb, j&otilde;udmata p&auml;randit vastu v&otilde;tta v&otilde;i sellest loobuda, on tema p&auml;rijatel &otilde;igus see p&auml;rand vastu v&otilde;tta v&otilde;i sellest loobuda sama t&auml;htaja jooksul, mille jooksul neil on &otilde;igus p&auml;rima &otilde;igustatud isikust j&auml;&auml;nud p&auml;rand vastu v&otilde;tta v&otilde;i sellest loobuda. </eesti>
<inglise>If a person entitled to succeed dies without being able to accept or renounce the succession, his or her successors have the right to accept or renounce the succession within the same term within which they have the right to accept or renounce the succession left by the person entitled to succeed. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 120. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 120. </inglise>
<eesti>Andmed p&auml;randi kohta </eesti>
<inglise>Information concerning estate </inglise>
<eesti>Enne p&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tmist v&otilde;i sellest loobumist on p&auml;rima &otilde;igustatud isikul &otilde;igus saada andmeid p&auml;randvara koosseisu ning testamendi ja p&auml;rimislepingu sisu kohta kohtult, notarilt ja muult isikult, kelle valduses on p&auml;randvara, testament v&otilde;i p&auml;rimisleping. </eesti>
<inglise>Before acceptance or renunciation of a succession, a person entitled to succeed has the right to receive information concerning the composition of the estate and the content of the will or testamentary contract from a court, notary or other person who possesses the estate, the will or testamentary contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 121. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 121. </inglise>
<eesti>Tingimusliku vastuv&otilde;tmise v&otilde;i loobumise lubamatus </eesti>
<inglise>Disallowance of conditional acceptance or renunciation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;randi tingimuslik vastuv&otilde;tmine v&otilde;i sellest tingimuslik loobumine ei ole lubatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A conditional acceptance or conditional renunciation of succession is not permitted. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui p&auml;rija on p&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tmiseks asunud valdama, kasutama v&otilde;i k&auml;sutama kas v&otilde;i osa p&auml;randvarast, loetakse, et ta on kogu p&auml;randi vastu v&otilde;tnud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If for acceptance of a succession a successor commences possession, use or disposal of even a share of the estate, the successor shall be deemed to have accepted the entire succession. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) P&auml;randi osalise vastuv&otilde;tmise v&otilde;i osalise loobumise avaldus, samuti p&auml;randi tingimusliku vastuv&otilde;tmise v&otilde;i sellest tingimusliku loobumise avaldus on t&uuml;hine. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An application for partial acceptance or partial renunciation of a succession or an application for conditional acceptance or conditional renunciation of a succession is void. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 122. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 122. </inglise>
<eesti>Eksimus p&auml;rimise alustes </eesti>
<inglise>Error in bases of succession </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui p&auml;rija on p&auml;randi vastu v&otilde;tnud v&otilde;i sellest loobunud eksimuse t&otilde;ttu selles, kas ta p&auml;rib seaduse, testamendi v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepingu j&auml;rgi, v&otilde;ib kohus tema n&otilde;udel tunnistada p&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tmise v&otilde;i sellest loobumise kehtetuks ja m&auml;&auml;rata p&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tmiseks v&otilde;i sellest loobumiseks uue t&auml;htaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a successor accepts or renounces a succession due to an error regarding whether the successor succeeds by intestate or testate succession or by testamentary contract, a court may declare the acceptance or renunciation of the succession invalid at the successor's request and specify a new term for acceptance or renunciation of the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui kohus on tunnistanud p&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tmise v&otilde;i sellest loobumise kehtetuks, loetakse, et p&auml;rija on saanud p&auml;rimis&otilde;igusest teada kohtuotsuse j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a court declares acceptance or renunciation of a succession invalid, the successor shall be deemed to become aware of the right of succession on the date of entry into force of the court judgement. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 123. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 123. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimine p&auml;randist loobumise korral </eesti>
<inglise>Succession in case of renunciation of succession </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui p&auml;rima &otilde;igustatud isik on p&auml;randist loobunud, on p&auml;rima &otilde;igustatud see isik, kes oleks p&auml;rinud siis, kui p&auml;randist loobunu oleks surnud enne p&auml;randi avanemist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a person entitled to succeed renounces a succession, the person who would have succeeded if the renouncer of the succession had died before the opening of the succession is entitled to succeed. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Isik, kes astub p&auml;randist loobunu asemele, v&otilde;ib p&auml;randi vastu v&otilde;tta v&otilde;i sellest loobuda sama t&auml;htaja jooksul, kui selleks oli &otilde;igus loobunul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person who replaces the renouncer of a succession may accept or renounce the succession within the same term that the renouncer had the right to accept or renounce. </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;htaega arvestatakse p&auml;evast, mil p&auml;randist loobunu asemele astuja loobumisest teada sai. </eesti>
<inglise>The term is calculated from the date the person who replaces the renouncer of the succession becomes aware of the renunciation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 124. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 124. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohalik omavalitsus&uuml;ksus ja riik </eesti>
<inglise>Local government and state </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Seadusj&auml;rgse p&auml;rimise korral ei saa kohalik omavalitsus&uuml;ksus ega riik p&auml;randist loobuda. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In the case of intestate succession, a local government or the state cannot renounce the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Seadusj&auml;rgse p&auml;rimise korral loetakse, et p&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tmise n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmisest olenemata on kohalik omavalitsus&uuml;ksus v&otilde;i riik p&auml;randi vastu v&otilde;tnud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the case of intestate succession, a local government or the state shall be deemed to accept the succession regardless of whether the requirements for acceptance of the succession are met. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 125. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 125. </inglise>
<eesti>V&otilde;lausaldaja &otilde;igus p&auml;randist loobumise korral </eesti>
<inglise>Rights of creditor in case of renunciation of succession </inglise>
<eesti>V&otilde;lausaldaja v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda, et p&auml;randist loobunu need v&otilde;lad, mida ei saa loobunu varast tasuda, tasutakse temal &otilde;iguse j&auml;rgi saada olevast p&auml;randiosast. </eesti>
<inglise>A creditor may demand that the debts of a renouncer of a succession which cannot be paid from the property of the renouncer be paid from the share of the estate to which the renouncer is entitled. </inglise>
<eesti>V&otilde;lgade rahuldamisest j&auml;rele j&auml;&auml;nud p&auml;randiosa l&auml;heb &uuml;le p&auml;rijatele, kes p&auml;rivad p&auml;randist loobunu asemel. </eesti>
<inglise>The residual estate remaining after satisfaction of the debts transfers to the successors who succeed in place of the renouncer of the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 126. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 126. </inglise>
<eesti>Annakust loobumine </eesti>
<inglise>Renunciation of legacy </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Annakust loobumist ei loeta p&auml;randist loobumiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Renunciation of a legacy shall not be deemed to be renunciation of a succession. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui annakusaaja annakust loobub, j&auml;&auml;b annak koos sellega seotud kohustustega isikule, kelle p&auml;randiosa arvel tuleb annak t&auml;ita, kui testamendist v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepingust ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a legatee renounces a legacy, the legacy together with the obligations relating thereto shall remain with the person out of whose share of the estate the legacy is executed unless otherwise provided by the will or testamentary contract. </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>Juurdekasvu&otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Right of Accretion </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 127. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 127. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randiosa suurenemine juurdekasvu&otilde;iguse alusel </eesti>
<inglise>Increase in share of estate on basis of right of accretion </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui p&auml;rija ei ole p&auml;randit vastu v&otilde;tnud ega p&auml;randist loobunud, jagatakse tema p&auml;randiosa juurdekasvu&otilde;iguse alusel p&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tnud p&auml;rijate vahel v&otilde;rdeliselt nende p&auml;randiosade suurusega, kui testamendist v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepingust ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a successor has not accepted or renounced the succession, the successor's share of the estate is divided on the basis of the right of accretion among the successors who have accepted the succession in proportion to the size of their shares of the estate unless otherwise provided by the will or testamentary contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Juurdekasvu&otilde;iguse alusel suureneb p&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tnud p&auml;rija p&auml;randiosa, s&otilde;ltumata tema n&otilde;usolekust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The share of the estate of a successor who has accepted the succession increases on the basis of the right of accretion regardless of the successor's consent. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Koos juurdekasvu&otilde;iguse alusel &uuml;lemineva p&auml;randiosaga l&auml;hevad &uuml;le ka sellel osal lasuvad annakud ja muud kohustused. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The legacies and other obligations incumbent on a share of an estate being transferred on the basis of the right of accretion also transfer together with the share. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 128. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 128. </inglise>
<eesti>Juurdekasvu&otilde;igus testamendi- v&otilde;i lepinguj&auml;rgsel p&auml;rimisel </eesti>
<inglise>Right of accretion upon testate succession or contractual succession </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui p&auml;randaja on testamendiga p&auml;randanud kogu oma vara p&auml;rijate osi m&auml;&auml;ramata, l&auml;heb juurdekasvu&otilde;iguse alusel &uuml;leminev p&auml;randiosa &uuml;le teistele testamendij&auml;rgsetele p&auml;rijatele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a bequeather bequeaths all his or her property by a will without specifying the shares of the successors, the share of the estate being transferred on the basis of the right of accretion transfers to the other testate successors. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui p&auml;randaja on lepinguga p&auml;randanud kogu oma vara p&auml;rijate osi m&auml;&auml;ramata, l&auml;heb juurdekasvu&otilde;iguse alusel &uuml;leminev p&auml;randiosa &uuml;le teistele lepinguj&auml;rgsetele p&auml;rijatele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a bequeather bequeaths all his or her property by a contract without specifying the shares of the successors, the share of the estate being transferred on the basis of the right of accretion transfers to the other contractual successors. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui p&auml;randaja on testamendi v&otilde;i lepinguga p&auml;randanud mitmele p&auml;rijale &uuml;hise osa oma varast iga p&auml;rija osa m&auml;&auml;ramata, j&auml;&auml;b see p&auml;randiosa juurdekasvu&otilde;iguse alusel teistele sama p&auml;randiosa p&auml;rijatele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a bequeather bequeaths a joint share of his or her property by a will or contract to several successors without specifying the share of each successor, the share of the estate remains with the other successors of the same share of the estate on the basis of the right of accretion. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 129. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 129. </inglise>
<eesti>Juurdekasvu&otilde;iguse kohaldamatus </eesti>
<inglise>Inapplicability of right of accretion </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Juurdekasvu&otilde;igust ei kohaldata, kui p&auml;randaja on selle testamendi v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepinguga keelanud v&otilde;i kui p&auml;randist loobumata ja p&auml;randi vastu v&otilde;tmata j&auml;tnud p&auml;rijal on asep&auml;rija. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The right of accretion does not apply if a bequeather prohibits it by a will or testamentary contract or if a successor who has not renounced or accepted the succession has an alternative successor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Sundosa p&auml;rijal ei ole &otilde;igust p&auml;rida juurdekasvu&otilde;iguse alusel, kui tal on &otilde;igus &uuml;ksnes sundosale. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A successor of a compulsory portion does not have the right to succeed on the basis of the right of accretion if the successor only has a right to the compulsory portion. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui seadus- v&otilde;i testamendij&auml;rgne p&auml;rija ei ole p&auml;randit vastu v&otilde;tnud ega sellest loobunud, ei ole lepinguj&auml;rgsel p&auml;rijal &otilde;igust p&auml;randile juurdekasvu&otilde;iguse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If an intestate or testate successor has not accepted or renounced the succession, a contractual successor does not have the right to the succession on the basis of the right of accretion. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui testamendi v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepinguga on p&auml;rijale m&auml;&auml;ratud kindel p&auml;randiosa ning p&auml;rija ei ole seda vastu v&otilde;tnud ega sellest loobunud, l&auml;heb see p&auml;randiosa &uuml;le p&auml;randaja seadusj&auml;rgsetele p&auml;rijatele. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a definite share of an estate is given to a successor by a will or testamentary contract and the successor has not accepted or renounced it, the share of the estate transfers to the intestate successors of the bequeather. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Juurdekasvu&otilde;igust ei kohaldata, kui p&auml;rima on &otilde;igustatud vaid &uuml;ks isik, kes ei ole p&auml;randit vastu v&otilde;tnud ega p&auml;randist loobunud. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The right of accretion does not apply if only one person is entitled to succeed and the person has not accepted or renounced the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>Sel juhul on p&auml;rima &otilde;igustatud see isik, kes oleks p&auml;rinud siis, kui p&auml;randi vastu v&otilde;tmata ja sellest loobumata j&auml;tnud isik oleks surnud enne p&auml;randi avanemist. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case, the person who would have succeeded if the person who did not accept or renounce the succession had died before the opening of the succession is entitled to succeed. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 5 s&auml;testatut kohaldatakse ka juhul, kui &uuml;kski seaduse j&auml;rgi p&auml;rima &otilde;igustatud isik ei v&otilde;ta p&auml;randit vastu ega loobu sellest. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The provisions of subsection (5) of this section also apply if no person who is entitled to succeed in intestacy accepts or renounces the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rija &otilde;igused ja kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Rights and Obligations of Successor </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 130. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 130. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randaja &otilde;iguste ja kohustuste &uuml;leminek </eesti>
<inglise>Transfer of rights and obligations of bequeather </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tmisega l&auml;hevad p&auml;rijale &uuml;le k&otilde;ik p&auml;randaja &otilde;igused ja kohustused, v&auml;lja arvatud need, mis oma olemuselt on lahutamatult seotud p&auml;randaja isikuga v&otilde;i mis seadusest tulenevalt ei saa &uuml;helt isikult teisele &uuml;le minna. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) With the acceptance of a succession, all rights and obligations of the bequeather transfer to the successor except those which by their nature are unseparably bound to the person of the bequeather or which pursuant to law do not transfer from one person to another. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Seaduses s&auml;testatud juhtudel v&otilde;ivad p&auml;randaja isikuga lahutamatult seotud &otilde;igused &uuml;le minna p&auml;rijale. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the cases provided by law, rights unseparably bound to the person of the bequeather may transfer to a successor. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui p&auml;randvarast ei piisa p&auml;randaja k&otilde;igi v&otilde;lgade tasumiseks ning ei ole tehtud p&auml;randi inventuuri ega p&auml;randvara eraldatud, on p&auml;rija kohustatud tasuma p&auml;randaja v&otilde;lad ka oma vara arvel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If an estate is insufficient for payment of all debts of the bequeather and an inventory of the estate has not been made nor has the estate been separated, a successor is required to pay the debts of the bequeather out of the successor's own property. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 131. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 131. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randaja matuse kulud </eesti>
<inglise>Funeral expenses of bequeather </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;rija kannab p&auml;randaja matuse kulud, arvestades tavasid ning p&auml;randi suurust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A successor shall bear the funeral expenses of the bequeather, considering custom and the size of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui p&auml;randvarast ei piisa p&auml;randaja matuse kuludeks, kannab p&auml;rija need kulud oma arvel. </eesti>
<inglise>If the estate is insufficient for the funeral expenses, the successor shall bear these expenses on the successor's own account. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Iga p&auml;rija kannab p&auml;randaja matuse kulud v&otilde;rdeliselt oma p&auml;randiosa suurusega, kui testamendist v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepingust ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Each successor shall bear the funeral expenses of the bequeather in proportion to the size of the successor's share of the estate unless otherwise provided by the will or testamentary contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) P&auml;randaja v&otilde;ib testamendis v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepingus m&auml;&auml;rata, kes tema matuse kulud kannab. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A bequeather may specify in a will or testamentary contract who shall bear his or her funeral expenses. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui p&auml;rija v&otilde;i annakusaaja p&auml;randvarast v&otilde;i annakust ei j&auml;tku p&auml;randaja matuse kuludeks, kannavad teised p&auml;rijad p&auml;randiosa v&otilde;i annakut &uuml;letavad matusekulud v&otilde;rdeliselt oma p&auml;randiosa suurusega. </eesti>
<inglise>If the estate or legacy of a successor or legatee is insufficient for the funeral expenses of the bequeather, the other successors shall bear the funeral expenses which exceed the share of the estate or the legacy in proportion to the size of their share of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 132. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 132. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randaja perekonnaliikmete &uuml;lalpidamise kulud </eesti>
<inglise>Expenditure for maintenance of family members of bequeather </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randaja perekonnaliikmetel, kes elasid p&auml;randaja surmani temaga koos ja said temalt &uuml;lalpidamist, on &otilde;igus &uuml;he kuu jooksul p&auml;rast p&auml;randaja surma j&auml;tkata &uuml;hise majapidamise esemete kasutamist ja saada p&auml;randi arvel &uuml;lalpidamist. </eesti>
<inglise>The family members of a bequeather who lived with him or her and received maintenance from him or her until the bequeather's death have the right to continue using the objects of the shared household and to receive maintenance out of the estate for one month after the death of the bequeather. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 133. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 133. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohustused testamendi ja p&auml;rimislepingu j&auml;rgi </eesti>
<inglise>Obligations by will and testamentary contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tnud p&auml;rija on kohustatud t&auml;itma testamendi v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepinguga etten&auml;htud korraldused, annakud, sihtk&auml;sundid, sihtm&auml;&auml;rangud ja muud kohustused. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A successor who accepts the succession is required to execute the dispositions, legacies, testamentary obligations, testamentary directions and other obligations provided by the will or testamentary contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&auml;rija peab v&otilde;imaldama kolmandatel isikutel t&auml;ita p&auml;randi arvel testamendist v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepingust tulenevaid korraldusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A successor shall allow third persons to execute dispositions out of the estate pursuant to the will or testamentary contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.99 j&otilde;ust.31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 134. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 134. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohustuste t&auml;itmise j&auml;rjekord </eesti>
<inglise>Order of performance of obligations </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;randi arvel t&auml;idetakse kohustused j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Obligations shall be performed out of the estate as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) esimeses j&auml;rjekorras tasutakse p&auml;randaja matuse, tema perekonnaliikmete &uuml;lalpidamise, p&auml;randi hoiu ja hooldamise ning inventuuri tegemise kulud; </eesti>
<inglise>1) in the first order, expenses are paid for the bequeather's funeral, maintenance of his or her family members, management and maintenance of the estate and the making of the inventory; </inglise>
<eesti>2) teises j&auml;rjekorras rahuldatakse v&otilde;lan&otilde;uded pankrotiseaduses (RT 1992, 31, 403) s&auml;testatud j&auml;rkude kaupa; </eesti>
<inglise>2) in the second order, claims for debts are satisfied in the stages provided for in the Bankruptcy Act (RT 1992, 31, 403); </inglise>
<eesti>3) kolmandas j&auml;rjekorras t&auml;idetakse annakud, sihtk&auml;sundid ja sihtm&auml;&auml;rangud. </eesti>
<inglise>3) in the third order, legacies, testamentary obligations and testamentary directions are executed. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) J&auml;rgmise j&auml;rjekorra kohustused t&auml;idetakse p&auml;rast eelmise j&auml;rjekorra kohustuste t&auml;ielikku t&auml;itmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The obligations of a subsequent order are performed after complete performance of the obligations of a preceding order. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui &uuml;he j&auml;rjekorra kohustuste t&auml;itmiseks ei j&auml;tku p&auml;randvara, t&auml;idetakse need p&auml;randvara arvel v&otilde;rdeliselt nende suurusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If an estate is insufficient for performance of the obligations of one order, these are performed out of the estate in proportion to their size. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) P&auml;randaja v&otilde;ib testamendis v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepingus panna kohustuse t&auml;itmise m&otilde;nele p&auml;rijale v&otilde;i annakusaajale, kuid ei v&otilde;i muuta k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1-3 s&auml;testatud kohustuste t&auml;itmise korda. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In a will or testamentary contract a bequeather may assign performance of an obligation to a successor or legatee but shall not change the procedure for performance of obligations provided for in subsections (1) -(3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 135. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 135. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rija vastutus p&auml;randi inventuuri korral </eesti>
<inglise>Liability of successor in case of inventory of estate </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui p&auml;rija p&auml;randit vastu v&otilde;ttes n&otilde;uab selle inventuuri, vabaneb ta p&auml;randaja v&otilde;lgade tasumise kohustusest oma vara arvel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If upon acceptance of a succession the successor demands an inventory of the estate, the successor is released from the obligation to pay the debts of the bequeather out of the successor's own property. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui p&auml;rija p&auml;rast inventuuri n&otilde;udmist loobub sellest n&otilde;udest, on ta kohustatud tasuma p&auml;randaja v&otilde;lad ka oma vara arvel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If after demanding an inventory a successor abandons the demand, the successor is also required to pay the debts of the bequeather out of the successor's own property. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 136. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 136. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohustuslik inventuur </eesti>
<inglise>Obligatory inventory </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;randi inventuur on kohustuslik, kui p&auml;rijaks on teov&otilde;imetu isik, kohalik omavalitsus&uuml;ksus v&otilde;i riik. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a person without active legal capacity, a local government or the state is a successor, an inventory of the estate is obligatory. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui teov&otilde;imetu p&auml;rija seaduslik esindaja ei ole p&auml;rija huvides p&auml;randi inventuuri taotlenud, vastutab ta oma varaga p&auml;randaja nende v&otilde;lgade eest, mille rahuldamiseks p&auml;randist ei j&auml;tkunud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the legal representative of a person without active legal capacity does not request an inventory of an estate in the interest of the successor, the legal representative is liable with the legal representative's own property for the debts of the bequeather which cannot be sufficiently satisfied from the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 137. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 137. </inglise>
<eesti>Inventuuri kord ja t&auml;htajad </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for and term of inventory </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;rija n&otilde;udel v&otilde;ib notar inventuuri tegemise teha &uuml;lesandeks p&auml;rijale, annakusaajale v&otilde;i teisele isikule, kes soovib p&auml;randist kasu saada, samuti testamendit&auml;itjale. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) At the request of a successor, a notary may assign the task of making an inventory to a successor, legatee or other person who wishes to receive benefit from the estate or to an executor of the will. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud isikutel ei ole &otilde;igust kaaluka p&otilde;hjuseta inventuuri tegemisest keelduda. </eesti>
<inglise>The persons specified do not have the right to refuse to make an inventory without good reason. </inglise>
<eesti>Notar v&otilde;ib teha inventuuri tegemise &uuml;lesandeks ka teisele isikule, kes n&otilde;ustub inventuuri tegema. </eesti>
<inglise>The notary may also assign the task of making an inventory to another person who consents to make the inventory. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.99 j&otilde;ust.31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Isikul, kellele notar on teinud &uuml;lesandeks inventuuri tegemise, on &otilde;igus saada p&auml;randvara kohta teavet krediidiasutustelt, samuti muult isikult, kelle valduses on p&auml;randvara v&otilde;i kellel on p&auml;randvara kohta andmeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person to whom a notary has assigned the task of making an inventory has the right to receive information concerning the estate from credit institutions and other persons who possess the estate or who have information concerning the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.99 j&otilde;ust.31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Inventuuri tegemiseks annab notar t&auml;htaja, mis ei v&otilde;i olla l&uuml;hem kui &uuml;ks kuu. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A notary shall provide a term for the making of an inventory which shall not be shorter than one month. </inglise>
<eesti>Notar v&otilde;ib inventuuri t&auml;htaega kaalukal p&otilde;hjusel pikendada, samuti vabastada inventuuri tegija sellest kohustusest. </eesti>
<inglise>The notary may extend the term of an inventory for good reason or release the maker of an inventory from the obligation. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.99 j&otilde;ust.31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Inventuuri k&auml;igus koostatakse p&auml;randvara nimekiri, kuhu kantakse k&otilde;ik p&auml;randi avanemise ajal olemasolevad p&auml;ritavad asjad ning &otilde;igused ja kohustused, samuti nende t&auml;histamiseks ning v&auml;&auml;rtuse kindlakstegemiseks vajalik kirjeldus ja hinnang. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In the course of making an inventory, an inventory of the estate is prepared which sets out all inheritable things, rights and obligations existing at the time of opening of the succession, their description and appraisal necessary for their designation and valuation. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randvara nimekiri esitatakse notarile. </eesti>
<inglise>The inventory of the estate shall be submitted to a notary. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.99 j&otilde;ust.31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui notarile on esitatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 4 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele vastav p&auml;randvara nimekiri, v&otilde;ib notar j&auml;tta inventuuri m&auml;&auml;ramata. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If the inventory of an estate which meets the requirements provided for in subsection (4) of this section is submitted to a notary, the notary need not order the making of an inventory. </inglise>
<eesti>Sel juhul loetakse, et inventuur on tehtud. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case, an inventory shall be deemed to have been made. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.99 j&otilde;ust.31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui inventuur on &uuml;he p&auml;rija n&otilde;udel tehtud, ei ole kaaluka p&otilde;hjuseta vaja teise p&auml;rija n&otilde;udel p&auml;randit uuesti inventeerida. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) If an inventory is made at the request of one successor, a new inventory of the estate is not required to be made at the request of another successor without good reason. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Inventuuri tegemise kulud h&uuml;vitatakse p&auml;randvara arvel. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The expenses for making an inventory are reimbursed out of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 138. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 138. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rija pahatahtlikkus p&auml;randi nimekirja koostamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Bad faith of successor upon preparation of inventory of estate </inglise>
<eesti>Kui p&auml;rija j&auml;tab p&auml;randvara nimekirja kandmiseks avaldamata p&auml;randi hulka kuuluvaid asju v&otilde;i &otilde;igusi v&otilde;i avaldab olematuid kohustusi selleks, et kahjustada p&auml;randaja v&otilde;lausaldajaid, vastutab p&auml;rija p&auml;randaja v&otilde;lgade eest ka oma varaga. </eesti>
<inglise>If a successor does not disclose things or rights forming part of the estate to be entered in the inventory of the estate or discloses non-existent obligations in order to damage the creditors of the bequeather, the successor is also liable for the debts of the bequeather with the successor's own property. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.99 j&otilde;ust.31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 138 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 138 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Inventuuritegija vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Liability of person making inventory </inglise>
<eesti>Kui inventuuritegija, kes ei ole p&auml;rija, tahtlikult ei kanna p&auml;randvara nimekirja p&auml;randi hulka kuuluvat asja v&otilde;i &otilde;igust v&otilde;i kannab p&auml;randvara nimekirja olematu kohustuse, kahjustamaks v&otilde;lausaldaja v&otilde;i teiste p&auml;randist kasu saama &otilde;igustatud isikute huve, vastutab ta tekitatud kahju eest. </eesti>
<inglise>If a person who is making an inventory and who is not a successor intentionally leaves things or rights which form part of the estate out of the inventory or enters non-existent obligations in the inventory in order to damage the interests of creditors or other persons entitled to receive benefit from the succession, he or she shall be liable for the damage caused. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.99 j&otilde;ust.31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 139. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 139. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randi v&auml;ljaandmine </eesti>
<inglise>Delivery of estate </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isik, kes valdab p&auml;randvara, kuid ei ole &otilde;igustatud p&auml;rima, on kohustatud p&auml;rijale, annakusaajale, testamendit&auml;itjale v&otilde;i p&auml;randvara hooldajale p&auml;randvara v&auml;lja andma. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person who possesses an estate but is not entitled to succeed is required to deliver the estate to a successor, legatee, executor of the will or administrator of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud isik on andnud p&auml;randvara hulka kuuluva asja isikule, kellele ta ei pidanuks andma, on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda asi v&auml;lja ka heauskselt valdajalt. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the person specified in subsection (1) of this section has given a thing which forms part of the estate to a person to whom the person should not have given it, the right exists to claim delivery even from a possessor in good faith. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) P&auml;randvara v&auml;lja andnud isikul on &otilde;igus &uuml;leantavast p&auml;randvarast maha arvata p&auml;randaja matuse kulud, mis on tema poolt tehtud, samuti seadusj&auml;rgsele p&auml;rijale ja testamendi ning p&auml;rimislepingu korralduste t&auml;itmiseks &uuml;leantu. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A person who delivers an estate has the right to deduct from the estate being transferred the bequeather's funeral expenses incurred by the person, that which was transferred to an intestate successor and that which was transferred for execution of the dispositions in the will or testamentary contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Koos p&auml;randiga l&auml;heb p&auml;rijale &uuml;le kohustus, mille p&auml;randvara vallanud isik pidi endale v&otilde;tma p&auml;randvara valdamise t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An obligation which the person who possessed an estate must assume themself due to possession of the estate transfers to a successor together with the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 140. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 140. </inglise>
<eesti>Eba&otilde;igete andmete esitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Submission of false information </inglise>
<eesti>Kui isik on teadlikult esitanud notarile v&otilde;i kohtule eba&otilde;igeid andmeid v&otilde;i varjanud teavet, v&otilde;ib temalt eba&otilde;igete andmete esitamise v&otilde;i teabe varjamise t&otilde;ttu p&auml;randvara arvel saadu igal ajal v&auml;lja n&otilde;uda. </eesti>
<inglise>If a person knowingly submits false information to a notary or a court or conceals information, the delivery of that which is received from an estate due to the submission of false information or concealing of information may be demanded from the person at any time. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 140 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 140 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimistunnistus </eesti>
<inglise>Succession certificate </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;rija v&otilde;i annakusaaja n&otilde;udel v&auml;ljastab notar p&auml;rimistunnistuse p&auml;randi vastu v&otilde;tnud p&auml;rijale v&otilde;i annakusaajale. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A notary shall issue a succession certificate to a successor or legatee at the request of the successor or legatee. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.99 j&otilde;ust.31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Notar v&auml;ljastab p&auml;rimistunnistuse, kui isiku p&auml;rimis&otilde;igus ja selle ulatus on piisavalt t&otilde;endatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A notary shall issue a succession certificate if sufficient proof is provided concerning the right of succession of a person and the extent thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.99 j&otilde;ust.31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) P&auml;rimistunnistuse annab v&auml;lja notar, kelle t&ouml;&ouml;piirkonda kuulub p&auml;randi avanemise koht. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A succession certificate shall be issued by the notary in whose territorial jurisdiction the place of the opening of the succession falls. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui p&auml;randi avanemise koht on v&auml;lismaal ja p&auml;rimisele kohaldatakse Eesti seadust, annab p&auml;rimistunnistuse v&auml;lja notar, kelle t&ouml;&ouml;piirkonnas asub p&auml;randvara. </eesti>
<inglise>If the place of the opening of a succession is in a foreign state and Estonian law applies to the succession, the succession certificate shall be issued by the notary in whose territorial jurisdiction the estate is located. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui p&auml;randvara asub mitme notari t&ouml;&ouml;piirkonnas, annab p&auml;rimistunnistuse v&auml;lja notar, kelle poole p&ouml;&ouml;rduti p&auml;rimistunnistuse v&auml;ljastamise avaldusega esimesena. </eesti>
<inglise>If the estate is located in the territorial jurisdictions of several notaries, the succession certificate shall be issued by the notary to whom an application for the issue of a succession certificate was first submitted. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.99 j&otilde;ust.31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Kaasp&auml;rijad </eesti>
<inglise>Co-successors </inglise>
<eesti>1. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 1 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 141. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 141. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaasp&auml;rijate &otilde;igussuhted </eesti>
<inglise>Legal relations of co-successors </inglise>
<eesti>Kui p&auml;randi on vastu v&otilde;tnud mitu p&auml;rijat (kaasp&auml;rijad), on p&auml;randvara nende kaasomandis. </eesti>
<inglise>If several successors have accepted the succession (co-successors), the estate is in their common ownership. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaasp&auml;rijad valdavad, kasutavad v&otilde;i k&auml;sutavad p&auml;randvara kaasomandi kohta k&auml;ivate s&auml;tete kohaselt v&otilde;i n&otilde;uavad p&auml;randvara jagamist. </eesti>
<inglise>The co-successors possess, use or dispose of the estate pursuant to the provisions concerning common ownership or demand division of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 142. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 142. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohustuste ja kulude jaotamine </eesti>
<inglise>Distribution of obligations and expenditure </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;randil lasuvad kohustused, samuti p&auml;randaja matuse, p&auml;randaja perekonnaliikmete &uuml;lalpidamise, p&auml;randi hoiu, hooldamise ja inventuuri kulud ning muud p&auml;randiga seoses tehtud vajalikud ja kasulikud kulutused jaotatakse kaasp&auml;rijate vahel v&otilde;rdeliselt nende p&auml;randiosaga, kui testamendist v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepingust ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The obligations incumbent on an estate and the expenses for the bequeather's funeral, maintenance of family members, management, maintenance and inventory of the estate, and other necessary and useful expenses incurred in connection with the estate shall be distributed among the co-successors in proportion to their share of the estate unless otherwise provided by the will or testamentary contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&auml;randi suhtes n&otilde;ude&otilde;igust omavate isikute ees vastutavad p&auml;rijad solidaarselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The successors are solidarily liable to persons with a right of claim with respect to the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui p&auml;rija on tasunud p&auml;randil lasunud v&otilde;la, on tal &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda kaasp&auml;rijatelt v&otilde;rdeliselt nende p&auml;randiosaga tema kohustust &uuml;letava v&otilde;laosa tasumist v&otilde;rdeliselt kaasp&auml;rijate p&auml;randiosaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a successor pays a debt incumbent on the succession, the successor has the right to demand from the successor's co-successors, in proportion to their shares of the succession, payment of the share of the debt exceeding the successor's obligation in proportion to the share of the succession of the co-successors. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 143. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 143. </inglise>
<eesti>V&otilde;lgniku vastutus kaasp&auml;rijate ees </eesti>
<inglise>Liability of debtor to co-successors </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isik, kellel on kohustus p&auml;randi suhtes, vastutab iga kaasp&auml;rija ees v&otilde;rdeliselt kaasp&auml;rija p&auml;randiosa suurusega, kui p&auml;randaja ei ole testamendis v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepinguga m&auml;&auml;ranud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person who has an obligation with respect to a succession is liable to each co-successor in proportion to the size of the co-successor's share of the succession unless the bequeather has provided otherwise in the will or testamentary contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud isik on kohustuse &uuml;he v&otilde;i mitme p&auml;rija ees t&auml;itnud ja ta ei teadnud ega pidanud teadma, et on teisi kaasp&auml;rijaid, loetakse ta kohustuse t&auml;itnuks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the person specified in subsection (1) of this section performs an obligation with respect to one or several successors and the person did not know and need not have known that there are other co-successors, the person shall be deemed to have performed the obligation. </inglise>
<eesti>2. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 2 </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randvara jagamine </eesti>
<inglise>Division of Estate </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 144. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 144. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randvara jagamise m&otilde;iste ja viis </eesti>
<inglise>Definition and manner of division of estate </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;randvara jagamisel m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks, millised p&auml;randi hulka kuuluvad asjad v&otilde;i nende osad, samuti &otilde;igused ja kohustused j&auml;&auml;vad igale kaasp&auml;rijale. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon division of an estate, which things or shares of things and which rights and obligations forming part of the estate transfer to each co-successor shall be determined. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&auml;randvara jagatakse p&auml;rijate vahel vastavalt nende osale, l&auml;htudes p&auml;randvara hulka kuuluvate asjade harilikust v&auml;&auml;rtusest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An estate shall be divided among successors according to their shares, based on the usual value of the things forming part of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rijate kokkuleppel v&otilde;ib p&auml;randvara hulka kuuluvat asja hinnata p&auml;rija erilise huvi alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>By agreement of the successors, a thing forming part of the estate may be valuated on the basis of the special interest of a successor. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) P&auml;randvara jagamisel kohaldatakse kaasomandis oleva asja jagamise s&auml;tteid, kui k&auml;esolevast seadusest ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon division of an estate, the provisions concerning division of a thing in common ownership apply unless otherwise provided by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kaasp&auml;rijad jagavad p&auml;randvara kokkuleppel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Co-successors shall divide an estate by agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>Vaidluse korral jagab p&auml;randvara p&auml;rija n&otilde;udel kohus. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of a dispute, a court shall divide the estate at the request of a successor. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 145. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 145. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randvara jagamise kokkuleppe vorm </eesti>
<inglise>Form of agreement on division of estate </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui jagatava p&auml;randvara hulka kuulub kinnisasi, tuleb p&auml;randvara jagamise leping s&otilde;lmida notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud vormis. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If an immovable forms part of an estate being divided, the agreement on division of the estate shall be entered into in notarised form. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui p&auml;randvara jagamise ajal on kas v&otilde;i &uuml;ks p&auml;rija teov&otilde;imetu, peab p&auml;randvara jagamise leping olema s&otilde;lmitud kirjalikus vormis. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If at the time of division of an estate even one successor is without active legal capacity, the agreement on division of the estate shall be entered into in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 146. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 146. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randvara osaline jagamine </eesti>
<inglise>Partial division of estate </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui p&auml;randvara jagatakse vaid &uuml;he v&otilde;i m&otilde;ne kaasp&auml;rija n&otilde;udel, j&auml;tkavad teised kaasp&auml;rijad p&auml;randvarast nendele j&auml;&auml;va osa &uuml;hist valdamist, kasutamist ja k&auml;sutamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If an estate is divided at the request of only one or several co-successors, the other co-successors continue joint possession, use and disposal of the share of the estate remaining with them. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) V&auml;hemalt kaks kaasp&auml;rijat v&otilde;ivad n&otilde;uda, et neile eraldataks &uuml;hine p&auml;randiosa, mille valdamist, kasutamist ja k&auml;sutamist nad j&auml;tkavad kaasomanikena. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) At least two co-successors may demand that a joint share of the estate be separated for them, which they continue to possess, use or dispose of as co-owners. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 147. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 147. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randvara jagamise piirangud </eesti>
<inglise>Restrictions on division of estate </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;randvara jagamist v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda p&auml;rast 30 p&auml;eva m&ouml;&ouml;dumist p&auml;randi avanemise p&auml;evast &uuml;ksnes tingimusel, et on teada k&otilde;ik p&auml;rijad. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Division of an estate may be demanded after thirty days after the date of opening of the succession only on the condition that all successors are known. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui p&auml;rijad on s&otilde;lminud kokkuleppe, et p&auml;randit teatud t&auml;htajal ei jagata, ei v&otilde;i p&auml;randit enne kokkulepitud t&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumist jagada. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If successors enter into an agreement that the estate is not to be divided during a particular term, the estate shall not be divided before expiry of the agreed term. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui t&auml;htajas ei ole kokku lepitud v&otilde;i on t&auml;htaeg pikem kui 10 aastat, loetakse t&auml;htajaks 10 aastat p&auml;randi avanemise p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>If a term is not agreed to or the term is longer than ten years, the term shall be deemed to be ten years after the date of opening of the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) P&auml;randvara ei v&otilde;i jagada testamendi v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepinguga m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An estate shall not be divided during the term specified by the will or testamentary contract. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui testamendi v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepinguga on p&auml;randvara jagamine keelatud t&auml;htaega m&auml;&auml;ramata v&otilde;i on t&auml;htaeg pikem kui 30 aastat, loetakse t&auml;htajaks 30 aastat p&auml;randi avanemise p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>If division of an estate is prohibited by the will or testamentary contract without specifying a term or if the term is longer than thirty years, the term shall be deemed to be thirty years after the date of opening of the succession. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 148. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 148. </inglise>
<eesti>Jagatav vara </eesti>
<inglise>Divisible property </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;randvara jagamisel arvatakse selle hulka ka eelp&auml;randina saadud vara ning vara, mille v&otilde;rra p&auml;randvara on p&auml;rast p&auml;randi avanemist suurenenud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon division of an estate, property received as a provisional succession and the property by which the estate is increased after the opening of the succession are also included as part of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&auml;randvara jagamisel v&otilde;etakse arvesse p&auml;randaja matuse kulud, p&auml;randaja perekonnaliikmete &uuml;lalpidamise, p&auml;randi hoiu ja hooldamise ning inventuuri kulud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon division of an estate, the bequeather's funeral expenses, the expenses for maintenance of the bequeather's family members, management and maintenance of the estate and the inventory shall be taken into account. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) P&auml;randvara jagamiseks on p&auml;rijad kohustatud avaldama jagatava vara kindlakstegemiseks ja p&auml;randi jagamiseks vajalikud andmed. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) For division of an estate, the successors are required to disclose information necessary for determination of the divisible property and for division of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 149. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 149. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randaja n&otilde;ue p&auml;rija vastu </eesti>
<inglise>Claim of bequeather against successor </inglise>
<eesti>Kui p&auml;randajal oli n&otilde;ue p&auml;rija vastu, tasaarvestatakse see p&auml;randvara jagamisel v&otilde;lgnikule &uuml;lemineva p&auml;randvara osast. </eesti>
<inglise>If a bequeather had a claim against a successor, it shall be set off upon division of the estate from the share of the estate transferred to the debtor. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 150. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 150. </inglise>
<eesti>Tasu p&auml;randaja abistamise eest </eesti>
<inglise>Remuneration for helping bequeather </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randaja laps, kes on kaasp&auml;rijaks ja on p&auml;randajat &uuml;hises majapidamises oma vara v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;ga oluliselt abistanud, v&otilde;ib p&auml;randi jagamisel n&otilde;uda selle eest p&auml;randvara arvel &otilde;iglast h&uuml;vitist. </eesti>
<inglise>A child of a bequeather who is a co-successor and has significantly helped the bequeather in a shared household with his or her property or work may upon division of the estate demand fair compensation therefor out of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 151. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 151. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randvara hulka kuuluvate asjade jaotamine </eesti>
<inglise>Distribution of things forming part of estate </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;randvara hulka kuuluvaid asju jaotades arvestatakse iga kaasp&auml;rija erivajadusi ja -huve ning kaasp&auml;rijate enamiku soove, samuti testamendist v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepingust tulenevat testaatori viimset tahet. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In the distribution of things forming part of an estate, the special needs and interests of each co-successor, the wishes of the majority of co-successors and the testamentary intention of the testator pursuant to the will or testamentary contract shall be considered. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&auml;randvara hulka kuuluv asi, mida ei saa jagada reaalosadeks v&otilde;i mille p&auml;rijate kaasomandisse j&auml;tmine ei v&otilde;imaldaks asja otstarbekalt kasutada, antakse &uuml;hele p&auml;rijale. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A thing forming part of an estate which cannot be divided into physical shares or a thing which if remaining in the common ownership of the successors could not be used purposefully shall be transferred to one successor. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui p&auml;rijad ei j&otilde;ua kokkuleppele, kellele k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud asi anda, otsustab p&auml;rija n&otilde;udel kohus vastavalt asjaoludele, kas anda asi kellelegi p&auml;rijatest v&otilde;i m&uuml;&uuml;a see avalikul v&otilde;i p&auml;rijatevahelisel enampakkumisel ja saadud raha jagada p&auml;rijate vahel v&otilde;rdeliselt nende p&auml;randiosa suurusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the successors fail to agree as to whom a thing specified in subsection (2) of this section shall be transferred, a court shall decide at the request of a successor according to the circumstances whether to transfer the thing to one of the successors or to sell the thing by public auction or auction among the successors and divide the money received among the successors in proportion to the size of their shares of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui p&auml;randvara jagamisel osutub &uuml;hele p&auml;rijale j&auml;&auml;va vara v&auml;&auml;rtus suuremaks tema p&auml;randiosast, on p&auml;rija kohustatud maksma teistele p&auml;rijatele rahalise h&uuml;vitise. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If upon division of an estate the value of the property remaining with a successor is greater than the successor's share of the estate, the successor is required to pay monetary compensation to the other successors. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kogumisse kuuluvaid asju ei v&otilde;i p&auml;randvara jagamisel &uuml;ksteisest eraldada, kui kas v&otilde;i &uuml;ks p&auml;rija on eraldamise vastu v&otilde;i kui testamendist v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepingust ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon division of an estate, things belonging to a set shall not be separated from one another if even one successor is opposed to the separation or unless otherwise provided by the will or testamentary contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 152. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 152. </inglise>
<eesti>Erilise m&auml;lestusv&auml;&auml;rtusega asjad </eesti>
<inglise>Things with special sentimental value </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Perekonnale erilise m&auml;lestusv&auml;&auml;rtusega asju p&auml;randvara jagamisel ei m&uuml;&uuml;da, kui kas v&otilde;i &uuml;ks p&auml;rija on selle vastu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon division of an estate, things with special sentimental value to a family shall not be sold if even one successor is opposed to the sale. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui kaasp&auml;rijad erilise m&auml;lestusv&auml;&auml;rtusega asjade jaotamises kokkuleppele ei j&otilde;ua, otsustab kohus p&auml;rija n&otilde;udel, kellele asi anda. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If co-successors fail to agree on distribution of things with special sentimental value, a court shall at the request of a successor decide to whom to transfer the things. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 153. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 153. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randvara hulka kuuluva kinnisasja jaotamine </eesti>
<inglise>Division of immovable forming part of estate </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randvara hulka kuuluva kinnisasja v&otilde;ib p&auml;rijate vahel jagada reaalosadeks, kui see ei ole vastuolus kinnisasja jagamise ja maakorralduse kohta k&auml;ivate s&auml;tetega. </eesti>
<inglise>An immovable forming part of an estate may be divided into physical shares among successors if this is not contrary to provisions concerning division of immovables and land readjustment. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 154. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 154. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randvara t&auml;iendav jagamine </eesti>
<inglise>Additional division of estate </inglise>
<eesti>Kui p&auml;randvara jagamise j&auml;rel ilmneb, et osa varast on j&auml;&auml;nud arvestamata, jagatakse t&auml;iendavalt ka see osa. </eesti>
<inglise>If after division of an estate it becomes evident that a share of the property has not been considered, the share shall also be divided. </inglise>
<eesti>3. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 3 </inglise>
<eesti>Eelp&auml;rand </eesti>
<inglise>Provisional Succession </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 155. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 155. </inglise>
<eesti>Eelp&auml;randi m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of provisional succession </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Eelp&auml;rand on vara, mille on kinkena saanud seadusj&auml;rgseks p&auml;rijaks olev alaneja sugulane teiste p&auml;rijatega p&auml;randajaks olevalt &uuml;hiselt &uuml;lenejalt sugulaselt selle eluajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A provisional succession is property which a descendant intestate successor has received with other successors as a gift from a common ascendant bequeather during the lifetime of the bequeather. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kingitud vara on eelp&auml;rand, kui p&auml;randaja on kinkimisel nii m&auml;&auml;ranud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Property received by gift is a provisional succession if the bequeather has so designated upon making the gift. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Eelp&auml;randi kohta s&auml;testatut kohaldatakse &uuml;ksnes seadusj&auml;rgsel p&auml;rimisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Provisions concerning provisional succession only apply upon intestate succession. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 156. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 156. </inglise>
<eesti>Eelp&auml;randi &uuml;leminek </eesti>
<inglise>Transfer of provisional succession </inglise>
<eesti>Kui eelp&auml;randi saanud alaneja sugulane suri p&auml;rast p&auml;randi avanemist v&otilde;i loobus p&auml;randist v&otilde;i ei ole p&auml;randit vastu v&otilde;tnud, loetakse, et eelp&auml;randi on saanud selle alaneja sugulase asemele astunud p&auml;rija. </eesti>
<inglise>If a descendant who receives a provisional succession dies after the opening of the succession or renounces or does not accept the succession, the successor who replaces the descendant shall be deemed to receive the provisional succession. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 157. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 157. </inglise>
<eesti>Eelp&auml;randi arvestamine </eesti>
<inglise>Consideration of provisional succession </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Jagatava p&auml;randi suuruse m&auml;&auml;ramisel arvestatakse eelp&auml;randi v&auml;&auml;rtust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In the determination of the size of an estate being divided, the value of a provisional succession shall be considered. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randvara hulka kuuluvate asjade jaotamisel arvestatakse, et eelp&auml;randi saanud p&auml;rija on eelp&auml;randile vastava osa p&auml;randist k&auml;tte saanud. </eesti>
<inglise>In the distribution of the things forming part of an estate, the successor who received a provisional succession shall be deemed to have received a share of the estate corresponding to the provisional succession. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui eelp&auml;rand on suurem selle saanud p&auml;rija p&auml;randiosast, ei ole p&auml;rija kohustatud p&auml;randiosa &uuml;letavat eelp&auml;randi osa teistele p&auml;rijatele h&uuml;vitama. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a provisional succession is larger than the share of the estate of the successor who received it, the successor is not required to compensate the other successors for the share of the provisional succession exceeding the share of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>Selle v&otilde;rra v&auml;heneb teiste p&auml;rijate p&auml;randvara jagamisel saadav osa. </eesti>
<inglise>The share receivable by the other successors decreases by this amount upon division of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Eelp&auml;randi saanud p&auml;rijal on &otilde;igus anda eelp&auml;rand jagatava p&auml;randvara hulka, kui eelp&auml;randi v&auml;&auml;rtus ei ole p&auml;rast selle saamist oluliselt v&auml;henenud. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A successor who receives a provisional succession has the right to include the provisional succession in the divisible estate if the value of the provisional succession has not significantly decreased after its receipt. </inglise>
<eesti>Sel juhul ei loeta kinki eelp&auml;randiks. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case, the gift shall not be deemed to be a provisional succession. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) P&auml;randi jagamisel ei arvestata eelp&auml;randina saadud vara, kui seda ei ole alles ning eelp&auml;rija ei ole sellest varast kasu saanud ega ole selle h&auml;vimises s&uuml;&uuml;di. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Upon division of an estate, property received as a provisional succession shall not be considered if it no longer exists and the provisional successor has not received benefit from the property and is not at fault for the destruction thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>7. osa </eesti>
<inglise>Part 7 </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimisregister </eesti>
<inglise>Succession Register </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 158. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 158. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimisregistri pidamine </eesti>
<inglise>Maintenance of succession register </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;rimisregistrisse kantakse andmed testamentide ja p&auml;rimislepingute kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Information concerning wills and testamentary contracts is entered in the succession register. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&auml;rimisregistri pidaja on Tallinna Linnakohus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Tallinn City Court shall maintain the succession register. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Justiitsministril on &otilde;igus anda m&auml;&auml;rusi p&auml;rimisregistri pidamise korra kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Ministry of Justice has the right to issue regulations concerning the procedure for maintenance of the succession register. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) P&auml;rimisregistrile ja selle pidamisele ei kohaldata andmekogude seadust (RT I 1997, 28, 423; 1998, 36/37, 552; 1999, 10, 155; 2000, 57, 373; 92, 597; 2001, 7, 17; 17, 77), kui k&auml;esolevast seadusest ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Databases Act (RT I 1997, 28, 423; 1998, 36/37, 552; 1999, 10, 155; 2000, 57, 373; 92, 597; 2001, 7, 17; 17, 77) does not apply to the succession register and maintenance thereof unless otherwise provided by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(06.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.07.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 56, 336) </eesti>
<inglise>(06.06.2001 entered into force 07.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 56, 336) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 159. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 159. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimisregistri kande alus </eesti>
<inglise>Basis for entry in succession register </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;rimisregistrisse tehakse kandeid registrile esitatavate teatiste alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Entries are made in the succession register on the basis of statements submitted to the register. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Notar on kohustatud esitama p&auml;rimisregistrile hiljemalt testamendi v&otilde;i p&auml;rimislepingu t&otilde;estamise v&otilde;i testamendi, sealhulgas &sect; 26 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud korras hoiule antud testamendi, hoiule v&otilde;i hoiult v&otilde;tmise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgneval esimesel t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval teatise j&auml;rgmiste andmetega: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) On the first working day following the date of notarisation of a will or testamentary contract, including a will deposited pursuant to the procedure specified in subsection 26 (2) of this Act, or of the taking into deposit or retrieval from deposit of a will, a notary is required to submit a statement with the following information: </inglise>
<eesti>1) p&auml;randaja ees- ja perekonnanimi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the given name and surname of the bequeather; </inglise>
<eesti>2) p&auml;randaja s&uuml;nniaeg ja -koht; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the date and place of birth of the bequeather; </inglise>
<eesti>3) registrisse kantava dokumendi liik (notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud testament, notari hoiule antud testament, testamendi notari hoiult v&otilde;tmise dokument, p&auml;rimisleping) ning dokumendi t&otilde;estamise v&otilde;i hoiulev&otilde;tmise kuup&auml;ev, aasta ning number notariaalregistri j&auml;rgi; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the type of document being entered in the register (notarised will, will deposited with notary, document for retrieval of will from deposit with notary, testamentary contract) and the date and year of notarisation or taking into deposit of the document and the number of the document according to the notarial register; </inglise>
<eesti>4) notari nimi ja tema b&uuml;roo aadress. </eesti>
<inglise>4) the name of the notary and the address of his or her office. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.99 j&otilde;ust.31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Abikaasade vastastikuse testamendi v&otilde;i selle t&uuml;histamise kohta esitab notar k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 toodud andmed kummagi abikaasa kohta eraldi. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A notary shall submit the information set out in subsection (2) of this section concerning a reciprocal will of spouses or its revocation for each spouse separately. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Notariaaltoiminguid tegema volitatud konsulaaresinduse ametiisik esitab p&auml;rimisregistrile teatisi k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An official of a consular representation who is authorised to perform notarial acts shall submit statements to the succession register pursuant to the procedure provided for in subsections (2) and (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kandeid koduste testamentide, nende muutmise v&otilde;i t&uuml;histamise kohta tehakse registrisse testaatorite teatiste v&otilde;i nende isikute teatiste alusel, kellele on testaator testamendi andnud hoidmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Entries concerning domestic wills, their alteration or revocation are made in the register on the basis of statements of testators or statements of persons to whom a testator has given a will for safe-keeping. </inglise>
<eesti>Teatises m&auml;rgitakse: </eesti>
<inglise>Such statement shall set out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) p&auml;randaja ees- ja perekonnanimi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the given name and surname of the bequeather; </inglise>
<eesti>2) p&auml;randaja s&uuml;nniaeg ja -koht; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the date and place of birth of the bequeather; </inglise>
<eesti>3) p&auml;randaja aadress; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the address of the bequeather; </inglise>
<eesti>4) arvelev&otilde;etava dokumendi liik (tunnistajate juuresolekul allakirjutatud v&otilde;i omak&auml;eliselt kirjutatud testament) ning koostamise kuup&auml;ev ja aasta; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the type of document being registered (a will signed in the presence of witnesses or a holographic will) and the date and year of preparation; </inglise>
<eesti>5) testamendi asukoht; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the location of the will; </inglise>
<eesti>6) kande tegemist taotleja ees- ja perekonnanimi ning aadress. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the given name, surname and address of the applicant for the making of the entry. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 160. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 160. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimisregistri kannete vorm </eesti>
<inglise>Form of entries of succession register </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 159 t&auml;hendatud teatiste alusel registrisse tehtavate kannete vormi kinnitab justiitsminister oma m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The form of entries to be made in the register on the basis of the statements referred to in &sect; 159 of this Act shall be approved by a regulation of the Minister of Justice. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&auml;iendavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse l&otilde;ikes 1 t&auml;hendatud kannetele v&otilde;ib justiitsminister ette n&auml;ha registrisse andmete kandmist, mis on vaja p&auml;rimisasjade lahendamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In addition to the entries referred to in subsection (1) of this Act, the Minister of Justice may prescribe entry of information in the register which is required in the settlement of succession matters. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 161. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 161. </inglise>
<eesti>Andmete saladuses hoidmine </eesti>
<inglise>Maintaining confidentiality of information </inglise>
<eesti>Registrisse testamendi ja p&auml;rimislepingu kohta kantud andmeid hoitakse kuni p&auml;randi avanemiseni saladuses. </eesti>
<inglise>The confidentiality of information entered in the register concerning wills and testamentary contracts is maintained until the opening of a succession. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 162. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 162. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimisregistrist teabe andmine </eesti>
<inglise>Provision of information from succession register </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Registrisse kantud andmete kohta antakse teavet p&auml;rast seda, kui p&auml;randaja surm on dokumentaalselt t&otilde;endatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Information concerning the information entered in the register is provided after the death of a bequeather is certified. </inglise>
<eesti>Abikaasade vastastikuse testamendi kohta antakse teavet p&auml;rast &uuml;he abikaasa surma. </eesti>
<inglise>Information concerning a reciprocal will of spouses is provided after the death of one spouse. </inglise>
<eesti>Teavet v&auml;ljastatakse registri tehnilise sekret&auml;ri allkirjaga. </eesti>
<inglise>Information is issued with the signature of a clerical secretary of the register. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&auml;rimisregistrist v&otilde;ivad k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 160 l&otilde;ikes 1 t&auml;hendatud kannete kohta teavet saada k&otilde;ik f&uuml;&uuml;silised ja juriidilised isikud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) All natural persons and legal persons may receive information concerning the entries referred to in subsection 160 (1) of this Act from the succession register. </inglise>
<eesti>8. osa </eesti>
<inglise>Part 8 </inglise>
<eesti>Rakenduss&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>Implementing Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 163. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 163. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse j&otilde;ustumine </eesti>
<inglise>Entry into force of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;rimisseadus j&otilde;ustub 1997. aasta 1. jaanuaril. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Law of Succession Act enters into force on 1 January 1997. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-d 158-162 ja 173 j&otilde;ustuvad &uuml;ldalustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Sections 158-162 and 173 of this Act enter into force on the general basis. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 164. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 164. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimisseaduse kohaldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Application of Law of Succession Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse s&auml;tteid kohaldatakse p&auml;randi suhtes, mis on avanenud p&auml;rast 1996. aasta 31. detsembrit. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The provisions of this Act apply to successions which are opened after 31 December 1996. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Enne 1997. aasta 1. jaanuari avanenud p&auml;randit p&auml;ritakse Eesti NSV tsiviilkoodeksi s&auml;tete kohaselt, kui rakenduss&auml;tetest ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A succession opened before 1 January 1997 is succeeded to pursuant to the provisions of the Estonian SSR Civil Code unless otherwise provided by the implementing provisions. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 165. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 165. </inglise>
<eesti>Testament </eesti>
<inglise>Will </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Enne 1997. aasta 1. jaanuari tehtud testament on kehtiv, kui see on tehtud koosk&otilde;las testamendi tegemise ajal kehtinud seadusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A will made before 1 January 1997 is valid if it is made in accordance with the law in force at the time of making the will. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Enne 1997. aasta 1. jaanuari tehtud testamendi teksti t&otilde;lgendamiseks kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-de 27-32 s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For interpretation of the text of a will made before 1 January 1997, the provisions of &sect;&sect; 27-32 of this Act apply. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Enne 1997. aasta 1. jaanuari avanenud p&auml;randi testamendij&auml;rgse p&auml;rimise korral kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 38 s&auml;tteid, kui testamenti t&auml;idetakse p&auml;rast 1996. aasta 31. detsembrit. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In the case of a testate succession opened before 1 January 1997, the provisions of &sect; 38 of this Act apply if the will is executed after 31 December 1996. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 166. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 166. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimisk&otilde;lbmatus </eesti>
<inglise>Unworthiness to succeed </inglise>
<eesti>Enne 1997. aasta 1. jaanuari avanenud p&auml;randi p&auml;rimisel kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 6 l&otilde;ike 1 punktide 1-4 s&auml;tteid, kui p&auml;rand v&otilde;etakse vastu p&auml;rast 1996. aasta 31. detsembrit. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon succession of a succession opened before 1 January 1997, the provisions of clauses 6 (1) 1-4 apply if the succession is accepted after 31 December 1996. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 167. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 167. </inglise>
<eesti>Annak </eesti>
<inglise>Legacy </inglise>
<eesti>Kui p&auml;rand on avanenud enne 1997. aasta 1. jaanuari ja annak t&auml;idetakse p&auml;rast 1996. aasta 31. detsembrit, kohaldatakse annaku t&auml;itmisel k&auml;eoleva seaduse &sect;-de 66-68 s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>If a succession is opened before 1 January 1997 and a legacy is executed after 31 December 1996, the provisions of &sect;&sect; 66-68 of this Act apply upon execution of the legacy. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 168. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 168. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohaliku omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse ja riigi p&auml;rimis&otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Right of succession of local government and state </inglise>
<eesti>Kui p&auml;rand on avanenud enne 1997. aasta 1. jaanuari ning ei ole seadus- ega testamendij&auml;rgseid p&auml;rijaid v&otilde;i &uuml;kski p&auml;rija ei ole p&auml;randit vastu v&otilde;tnud ja p&auml;randvara ei ole riigile &uuml;le l&auml;inud, kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 18 s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>If a succession is opened before 1 January 1997 and there are no intestate or testate successors or no successor has accepted the succession and the estate has not transferred to the state, the provisions of &sect; 18 of this Act apply. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 169. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 169. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohustuste t&auml;itmise j&auml;rjekord </eesti>
<inglise>Order of performance of obligations </inglise>
<eesti>Kui p&auml;rand on avanenud enne 1997. aasta 1. jaanuari ja kohustus t&auml;idetakse p&auml;randi arvel p&auml;rast 1996. aasta 31. detsembrit, kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 134 s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>If a succession is opened before 1 January 1997 and an obligation is performed out of the estate after 31 December 1996, the provisions of &sect; 134 of this Act apply. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 170. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 170. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaasp&auml;rijate &otilde;igussuhted </eesti>
<inglise>Legal relations of co-successors </inglise>
<eesti>Kui p&auml;rand on avanenud enne 1997. aasta 1. jaanuari ja kaasp&auml;rijate &otilde;igusi teostatakse, kohustusi t&auml;idetakse v&otilde;i p&auml;randvara jagatakse p&auml;rast 1996. aasta 31. detsembrit, kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-de 141, 142 l&otilde;igete 1 ja 2, 144-149 ning 151-154 s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>If a succession is opened before 1 January 1997 and the rights of co-successors are exercised, their obligations are performed or the estate is divided after 31 December 1996, the provisions of &sect; 141, subsections 142 (1) and (2), &sect;&sect; 144-149 and 151-154 of this Act apply. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 171. (Kehtetu - 10.11.99 j&otilde;ust.31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 171. (Repealed - 10.11.99 entered into force 31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 172. (Kehtetu - 10.11.99 j&otilde;ust.31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 172. (Repealed - 10.11.99 entered into force 31.12.99 - RT I 1999, 88, 807) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 173. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 173. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rimisregistri asutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Establishment of succession register </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;rimisregister alustab tegevust 1996. aasta 1. oktoobril ning v&auml;ljastab registri kannete alusel teavet alates 1997. aasta 1. jaanuarist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The succession register commences operation on 1 October 1996 and issues information on the basis of the register entries as of 1 January 1997. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Notarid esitavad p&auml;rimisregistrile 1996. aasta 1. oktoobriks andmed nende poolt t&otilde;estatud testamentide kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Notaries shall submit information concerning wills attested to by them to the succession register by 1 October 1996. </inglise>
<eesti>Andmete vormi kinnitab justiitsminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The form of the information shall be approved by the Minister of Justice. </inglise>
<eesti>Samast t&auml;htp&auml;evast hakkavad notarid ja konsulaaresinduste ametiisikud esitama p&auml;rimisregistrile &sect; 159 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud teatisi. </eesti>
<inglise>As of the same date, notaries and officials of consular representations shall begin submitting the statements specified in subsection 159 (2) to the succession register. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 174. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 174. </inglise>
<eesti>Muudetud ja kehtivuse kaotanud &otilde;igusaktid </eesti>
<inglise>Amended and repealed legislation </inglise>
